WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:25.754 --> 00:00:27.255
[plane propellers whirring]

3
00:00:56.409 --> 00:00:57.660
[engine slowing down]

4
00:01:06.211 --> 00:01:07.378
[breathing heavily]

5
00:01:18.098 --> 00:01:19.098
{\an8}ODO ISLAND NAVY DETACHMENT

6
00:01:19.099 --> 00:01:21.059
- [man 1] Ready? One. two...
- [man 2] One. two...

7
00:01:22.227 --> 00:01:23.227
One...

8
00:01:23.645 --> 00:01:25.771
- Nothing wrong with the engine.
- [man 3] Roger.

9
00:01:25.772 --> 00:01:28.233
- No issues with the fuel line.
- [man 3] Understood.

10
00:01:36.533 --> 00:01:37.992
Ensign Shikishima. right?

11
00:01:39.744 --> 00:01:41.870
I was a mechanic at the
Tsukuba Naval Air Corps.

12
00:01:41.871 --> 00:01:44.081
Tachibana. We were
there at the same time.

13
00:01:44.082 --> 00:01:48.128
Tachibana? Oh. of course.
yes. I owe you and your men.

14
00:01:49.546 --> 00:01:50.588
[Tachibana sighs]

15
00:01:51.506 --> 00:01:53.966
This runway of ours is
chock-full of holes.

16
00:01:53.967 --> 00:01:56.010
and you were still
able to land safely.

17
00:01:57.303 --> 00:01:59.304
You haven't lost your
touch since we last met.

18
00:01:59.305 --> 00:02:02.516
[chuckles] Well. training
for dogfights was simple.

19
00:02:02.517 --> 00:02:04.602
It's different in
a real kamikaze.

20
00:02:06.813 --> 00:02:08.147
Yes. it is.

21
00:02:08.148 --> 00:02:10.567
Lucky you got this extra
chance to rest. huh?

22
00:02:13.236 --> 00:02:14.320
It's strange.

23
00:02:15.238 --> 00:02:16.655
Your rig. we looked it over.

24
00:02:16.656 --> 00:02:19.617
And not a single one of us
could pin down any issues.

25
00:02:21.244 --> 00:02:24.330
[exhales nervously] What
are you trying to say?

26
00:02:48.313 --> 00:02:49.480
I'm on your side.

27
00:02:50.440 --> 00:02:52.150
We need more people like you.

28
00:02:59.240 --> 00:03:01.408
I just don't see
what the point is.

29
00:03:01.409 --> 00:03:05.038
We know how this war is gonna
end. so why "die honorably" now?

30
00:03:14.589 --> 00:03:15.589
[sighs]

31
00:03:25.099 --> 00:03:26.475
[inhales deeply]

32
00:03:26.476 --> 00:03:27.852
[water lapping gently]

33
00:03:29.187 --> 00:03:30.563
[sighs]

34
00:03:31.898 --> 00:03:34.317
[water plopping]

35
00:03:55.630 --> 00:03:57.882
[air-raid siren blaring]

36
00:04:00.885 --> 00:04:01.719
Get the guns!

37
00:04:01.720 --> 00:04:03.096
- Yes. sir!
- Roger!

38
00:04:04.305 --> 00:04:05.722
- Is it a raid?
- [man 4] I don't know!

39
00:04:05.723 --> 00:04:08.642
- [man 5] What do you mean?
- We can't see. It's too dark!

40
00:04:08.643 --> 00:04:10.143
Is it the Americans again?

41
00:04:10.144 --> 00:04:11.771
- [distant snarling]
- [all gasp]

42
00:04:14.023 --> 00:04:15.024
[distant crashing]

43
00:04:15.566 --> 00:04:17.694
Taki! Taki!

44
00:04:18.278 --> 00:04:20.237
- Get a light on this!
- Roger!

45
00:04:20.238 --> 00:04:21.781
[crashing]

46
00:04:23.032 --> 00:04:25.701
- [snarling]
- [Taki yelps]

47
00:04:25.702 --> 00:04:27.537
- [panicked yelping]
- [footsteps approaching]

48
00:04:28.705 --> 00:04:29.664
[Taki screams]

49
00:04:29.665 --> 00:04:30.873
[snarling]

50
00:04:31.916 --> 00:04:33.001
[shocked whimpering]

51
00:04:33.668 --> 00:04:35.002
- Taki!
- Taki-san!

52
00:04:35.003 --> 00:04:36.712
What the hell is that thing?

53
00:04:36.713 --> 00:04:37.880
It's called Godzilla.

54
00:04:38.548 --> 00:04:41.008
- What's Godzilla?
- [man 6] One of the locals told me.

55
00:04:41.009 --> 00:04:43.970
When deep sea fish float
like today. Godzilla is near.

56
00:04:44.595 --> 00:04:45.972
[hesitates] Godzilla?

57
00:04:47.932 --> 00:04:49.099
[soldiers gasping]

58
00:04:49.100 --> 00:04:51.561
[roaring]

59
00:04:52.061 --> 00:04:53.146
We're done for.

60
00:04:53.813 --> 00:04:56.356
- Go! Take cover!
- Go! Get in the trenches!

61
00:04:56.357 --> 00:04:57.941
- Now! Go!
- [panicked screaming]

62
00:04:57.942 --> 00:05:00.820
[Godzilla snarling]

63
00:05:02.655 --> 00:05:04.698
[man 7] Hurry! Hurry!

64
00:05:04.699 --> 00:05:06.326
[panicked murmuring]

65
00:05:08.077 --> 00:05:09.537
What the hell is that thing?

66
00:05:10.121 --> 00:05:11.371
No one knows what it is.

67
00:05:11.372 --> 00:05:12.623
[footstep rumbles]

68
00:05:13.207 --> 00:05:15.209
- I have an idea.
- What is it?

69
00:05:16.586 --> 00:05:18.671
Think you can reach
your 20 mm gun?

70
00:05:19.422 --> 00:05:21.256
You're the only one
who knows how to shoot.

71
00:05:21.257 --> 00:05:22.799
We're just mechanics.

72
00:05:22.800 --> 00:05:24.010
It's gigantic.

73
00:05:24.510 --> 00:05:26.595
What if it doesn't work
and just makes it angrier?

74
00:05:26.596 --> 00:05:29.765
- A 20 mm gun's enough to kill anything!
- [footsteps approaching]

75
00:05:29.766 --> 00:05:32.060
Now go. hurry. It's
still heading this way.

76
00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:34.562
Hurry! Get out there!

77
00:05:35.271 --> 00:05:36.271
Go!

78
00:05:37.440 --> 00:05:38.440
Hurry!

79
00:05:39.192 --> 00:05:40.817
[breathing heavily]

80
00:05:40.818 --> 00:05:42.362
[tense music playing]

81
00:05:45.782 --> 00:05:46.823
[Godzilla huffs]

82
00:05:46.824 --> 00:05:48.534
[Shikishima breathing heavily]

83
00:05:51.454 --> 00:05:52.497
Get in!

84
00:05:58.503 --> 00:06:02.548
[Godzilla growling]

85
00:06:07.762 --> 00:06:09.138
Does he need an invitation?

86
00:06:12.183 --> 00:06:13.726
[Godzilla growling softly]

87
00:06:14.644 --> 00:06:16.603
[footstep rumbles]

88
00:06:16.604 --> 00:06:18.231
Come on! Shoot!

89
00:06:21.359 --> 00:06:24.278
[Godzilla snarling]

90
00:06:31.994 --> 00:06:33.413
It's still coming!

91
00:06:34.705 --> 00:06:38.251
- What do we do. Tachibana?
- We need ammo! Go get some rounds.

92
00:06:40.711 --> 00:06:42.337
[man 5 panting]

93
00:06:42.338 --> 00:06:43.922
[yelling fearfully]

94
00:06:43.923 --> 00:06:45.006
[Godzilla grunts]

95
00:06:45.007 --> 00:06:47.342
You idiots! Don't shoot!

96
00:06:47.343 --> 00:06:48.385
[mechanics screaming]

97
00:06:48.386 --> 00:06:50.471
[Tachibana] What are
you doing? Cease fire!

98
00:06:52.974 --> 00:06:54.267
[roaring angrily]

99
00:06:56.227 --> 00:06:58.812
Go! Get out! Get out!

100
00:06:58.813 --> 00:07:00.147
Fall back!

101
00:07:00.148 --> 00:07:02.233
- [panicked chattering]
- [pained yelping]

102
00:07:02.859 --> 00:07:04.277
[gasping fearfully]

103
00:07:05.361 --> 00:07:06.446
Tachibana!

104
00:07:07.989 --> 00:07:09.364
[pained grunting]

105
00:07:09.365 --> 00:07:11.116
[man 5 screaming]

106
00:07:11.117 --> 00:07:13.077
[gunfire]

107
00:07:13.619 --> 00:07:14.870
[man 6] Shoot it!

108
00:07:14.871 --> 00:07:17.080
[panicked squealing. gasping]

109
00:07:17.081 --> 00:07:18.583
[dramatic music playing]

110
00:07:23.671 --> 00:07:25.756
[mechanics whimpering]

111
00:07:28.593 --> 00:07:29.594
[gunfire]

112
00:07:32.680 --> 00:07:33.805
[man 8] Tomita!

113
00:07:33.806 --> 00:07:35.141
[whimpering]

114
00:07:38.186 --> 00:07:39.896
[distraught sobbing]

115
00:07:42.315 --> 00:07:43.858
[hyperventilating]

116
00:07:46.152 --> 00:07:47.527
I'll draw it this way.

117
00:07:47.528 --> 00:07:48.779
Shoot to kill!

118
00:07:49.447 --> 00:07:50.656
[screaming]

119
00:07:51.282 --> 00:07:52.825
[yelping fearfully]

120
00:07:54.994 --> 00:07:57.205
- [metal crunching]
- [glass shattering]

121
00:08:00.791 --> 00:08:01.834
[grunts]

122
00:08:02.668 --> 00:08:03.878
[pained gasping]

123
00:08:11.552 --> 00:08:14.138
[Godzilla roaring angrily]

124
00:08:16.140 --> 00:08:18.059
[sound fading]

125
00:08:19.810 --> 00:08:21.229
[music fades]

126
00:08:23.189 --> 00:08:24.357
[groans softly]

127
00:08:27.693 --> 00:08:29.487
[breathing heavily]

128
00:08:53.177 --> 00:08:55.054
[breathing rapidly]

129
00:09:01.477 --> 00:09:02.520
[strained grunting]

130
00:09:03.020 --> 00:09:05.106
[Tachibana] You boys
didn't deserve this.

131
00:09:07.066 --> 00:09:08.276
[strained panting]

132
00:09:16.409 --> 00:09:17.409
Hey!

133
00:09:20.246 --> 00:09:21.246
Hey.

134
00:09:26.002 --> 00:09:27.753
Yeah. that's right. Take a look!

135
00:09:29.880 --> 00:09:31.381
Everyone is dead!

136
00:09:31.382 --> 00:09:32.967
[disquieting music playing]

137
00:09:33.676 --> 00:09:36.387
Huh? All because
you didn't shoot!

138
00:09:37.471 --> 00:09:39.098
[Tachibana hyperventilating]

139
00:09:41.100 --> 00:09:42.226
Goddamn it!

140
00:09:49.650 --> 00:09:50.693
[Tachibana sobs]

141
00:09:55.114 --> 00:09:56.782
[disquieting music continues]

142
00:10:21.140 --> 00:10:22.140
[Tachibana] You.

143
00:10:22.975 --> 00:10:23.975
Hey!

144
00:10:44.705 --> 00:10:45.790
[grunts] Move.

145
00:11:01.931 --> 00:11:03.766
[disquieting music continues]

146
00:11:05.559 --> 00:11:07.895
- [man 1] Make sure it's not too loose.
- [man 2] Yes.

147
00:11:08.396 --> 00:11:11.190
[man 1] Yeah. that should
hold. Okay. let's go.

148
00:11:12.692 --> 00:11:14.068
[music building]

149
00:11:20.324 --> 00:11:22.243
[woman] Koichi? Is that you?

150
00:11:25.496 --> 00:11:26.664
Oh. Sumiko.

151
00:11:27.415 --> 00:11:29.041
I thought you were dead.

152
00:11:31.127 --> 00:11:32.920
Weren't you a kamikaze pilot?

153
00:11:40.094 --> 00:11:43.139
You have the nerve to come
back and show your face here?

154
00:11:43.806 --> 00:11:45.349
You disgraced us all!

155
00:11:46.767 --> 00:11:47.851
Take a look around.

156
00:11:47.852 --> 00:11:51.063
Do you see what happened to us
because of cowards like you?

157
00:11:53.357 --> 00:11:55.901
If you'd all done what
you were supposed to do.

158
00:11:56.944 --> 00:11:58.779
I'd still have my kids.

159
00:12:08.622 --> 00:12:11.584
Are my parents alive? Do you
know if they made it out?

160
00:12:18.716 --> 00:12:20.217
Everyone's dead.

161
00:12:23.053 --> 00:12:26.724
During the air raids. there was
fire covering this whole block.

162
00:12:29.477 --> 00:12:32.021
Your parents are dead.
Along with everyone.

163
00:12:34.690 --> 00:12:38.068
Including my children. who
met the very same fate.

164
00:12:51.165 --> 00:12:54.084
MY DEAREST SON. KOICHI...

165
00:12:56.003 --> 00:12:57.630
"Return to us alive."

166
00:13:01.342 --> 00:13:02.885
Isn't that what you wanted?

167
00:13:07.515 --> 00:13:09.225
[indistinct background chatter]

168
00:13:15.397 --> 00:13:17.107
- Is it good?
- [man 1] Not bad.

169
00:13:19.235 --> 00:13:20.778
[man 2] Stop! Stop. thief!

170
00:13:21.612 --> 00:13:24.113
- [woman 1] Out of my way!
- [man 2] Move! Move!

171
00:13:24.114 --> 00:13:25.448
[woman 1] Let me through!

172
00:13:25.449 --> 00:13:26.825
[man 1] Grab that woman!

173
00:13:26.826 --> 00:13:27.867
Hold on.

174
00:13:27.868 --> 00:13:29.619
[crowd gasping. jeering]

175
00:13:29.620 --> 00:13:31.079
- [woman 1] Take this!
- What?

176
00:13:31.080 --> 00:13:34.582
- [man 2] Hey! That's her! Get back here!
- [man 3] Catch that woman!

177
00:13:34.583 --> 00:13:36.001
[man 2] Thief!

178
00:13:36.585 --> 00:13:37.545
[baby gurgling]

179
00:13:37.546 --> 00:13:38.879
What on earth?

180
00:13:45.052 --> 00:13:47.471
- [baby whimpering]
- [women chattering]

181
00:13:49.306 --> 00:13:51.683
- Give everyone my love.
- Yes. good to see you.

182
00:13:51.684 --> 00:13:52.810
Hello.

183
00:13:53.310 --> 00:13:54.395
[baby cooing]

184
00:13:57.314 --> 00:13:59.774
[woman 2] Okay. Take
care of yourself.

185
00:13:59.775 --> 00:14:00.818
[woman 3] Bye!

186
00:14:04.196 --> 00:14:05.281
[sighs]

187
00:14:07.867 --> 00:14:08.909
Hello again!

188
00:14:10.494 --> 00:14:11.494
[Shikishima sighs]

189
00:14:12.788 --> 00:14:14.832
Thank goodness. Where were you?

190
00:14:16.375 --> 00:14:19.168
Hey. it's your own fault. I
couldn't just go out there.

191
00:14:19.169 --> 00:14:20.713
Too many lookie-loo's.

192
00:14:21.422 --> 00:14:23.799
So you've been here
watching the whole time?

193
00:14:24.800 --> 00:14:27.761
Yeah. I was starting to get
sick of waiting for you to move.

194
00:14:28.262 --> 00:14:29.262
Wasn't I?

195
00:14:30.097 --> 00:14:32.057
I bet you're hungry
now. aren't you?

196
00:14:32.600 --> 00:14:33.600
[chuckles softly]

197
00:14:35.102 --> 00:14:37.563
I thought you'd just leave
her there. Why didn't you?

198
00:14:38.397 --> 00:14:39.397
Hey!

199
00:14:41.275 --> 00:14:44.445
[Shikishima] I couldn't leave a
baby alone in a place like that.

200
00:14:46.989 --> 00:14:47.989
[woman 1] Oh?

201
00:14:49.867 --> 00:14:51.118
Oh really?

202
00:14:54.830 --> 00:14:56.624
Could you please
stop following me?

203
00:14:57.124 --> 00:14:59.959
[woman 1] But we'll die if
you leave us out here alone.

204
00:14:59.960 --> 00:15:01.295
Why would I care?

205
00:15:07.176 --> 00:15:09.637
After you're done eating.
would you please leave?

206
00:15:10.179 --> 00:15:13.307
Oh. you hear that? He's so
mean and scary. isn't he?

207
00:15:17.186 --> 00:15:18.687
Where's your husband. anyway?

208
00:15:19.396 --> 00:15:20.731
Did he fight in the war?

209
00:15:22.066 --> 00:15:25.068
What a question. Does it
look like I have a husband?

210
00:15:25.069 --> 00:15:26.069
What?

211
00:15:26.904 --> 00:15:28.030
Whose kid is she?

212
00:15:29.865 --> 00:15:32.576
- Does it matter?
- Of course it matters!

213
00:15:36.497 --> 00:15:38.707
[woman 1] It was during
one of the air raids.

214
00:15:39.917 --> 00:15:42.002
Her dying mother
asked me to take her.

215
00:15:44.129 --> 00:15:48.509
So... are you saying
you're not related to her?

216
00:15:49.677 --> 00:15:50.928
No. And so what?

217
00:15:54.056 --> 00:15:55.432
Are you insane?

218
00:15:56.266 --> 00:15:59.477
You have no business trying to take
care of a baby in the state you're in.

219
00:15:59.478 --> 00:16:02.106
- [woman 1] You're one to talk.
- [Shikishima] Hey!

220
00:16:08.904 --> 00:16:09.904
What's her name?

221
00:16:13.492 --> 00:16:15.494
AKIKO

222
00:16:16.829 --> 00:16:18.122
And what do I call you?

223
00:16:20.874 --> 00:16:21.874
Noriko.

224
00:16:25.087 --> 00:16:27.088
Why do you go around
dressed like that?

225
00:16:27.089 --> 00:16:29.591
You look like you spend
your days begging for money.

226
00:16:30.175 --> 00:16:31.843
Am I supposed to
be a whore instead?

227
00:16:31.844 --> 00:16:33.595
That's not what I said. but

228
00:16:35.139 --> 00:16:36.556
we're all trying to survive.

229
00:16:36.557 --> 00:16:38.767
If you were. I wouldn't
think less of you.

230
00:16:44.940 --> 00:16:45.983
Any family?

231
00:16:54.908 --> 00:16:56.284
HARU SHIKISHIMA
EIICHIRO SHIKISHIMA

232
00:16:56.285 --> 00:16:57.703
[Noriko] Your parents?

233
00:17:02.166 --> 00:17:03.166
Yeah.

234
00:17:04.877 --> 00:17:05.919
They were killed.

235
00:17:06.795 --> 00:17:07.921
In the air raids.

236
00:17:12.468 --> 00:17:14.386
So you're by
yourself now as well.

237
00:17:33.822 --> 00:17:34.698
[Shikishima] Huh?

238
00:17:34.699 --> 00:17:36.742
What? You can't stay here.

239
00:17:38.410 --> 00:17:39.828
Are you kidding me?

240
00:17:43.082 --> 00:17:44.082
[sighs]

241
00:17:54.218 --> 00:17:55.219
[Sumiko] Hey.

242
00:17:57.596 --> 00:17:59.056
What's the story. huh?

243
00:18:00.724 --> 00:18:03.560
- What story?
- [Sumiko] Don't play dumb with me.

244
00:18:04.520 --> 00:18:06.939
That mother and child
you took in last night.

245
00:18:07.439 --> 00:18:09.857
What. so now you think
you're some kind of saint?

246
00:18:09.858 --> 00:18:10.984
[Shikishima sighs]

247
00:18:11.819 --> 00:18:13.570
I didn't even want them to stay.

248
00:18:14.404 --> 00:18:17.574
What difference does that
make? You didn't kick them out.

249
00:18:19.618 --> 00:18:20.619
[sighs wearily]

250
00:18:21.829 --> 00:18:23.705
It's too late to play the hero.

251
00:18:25.624 --> 00:18:27.625
I see right through you.

252
00:18:27.626 --> 00:18:29.670
Don't bother asking me for help.

253
00:18:34.842 --> 00:18:35.842
Wait.

254
00:18:37.386 --> 00:18:40.139
The girl. Do you know
if she can breastfeed?

255
00:18:41.890 --> 00:18:43.432
No. she's...

256
00:18:43.433 --> 00:18:46.395
The child. she isn't the mother.

257
00:18:48.021 --> 00:18:49.273
What are you saying?

258
00:18:49.773 --> 00:18:51.024
[Sumiko] Oh-ho-ho-ho-ho.

259
00:18:51.692 --> 00:18:53.569
Hmm? Mm-hmm.

260
00:18:56.864 --> 00:18:57.948
There you go.

261
00:18:59.825 --> 00:19:00.826
[sighs]

262
00:19:01.743 --> 00:19:04.830
If you keep feeding her like
this. she'll die of malnutrition.

263
00:19:05.330 --> 00:19:07.416
Right? Ah.

264
00:19:08.625 --> 00:19:12.004
So you take in a child. but you
have no idea how to care for it.

265
00:19:12.796 --> 00:19:14.214
What were you thinking?

266
00:19:14.965 --> 00:19:16.341
I'm not sure.

267
00:19:20.596 --> 00:19:21.596
[Sumiko sighs]

268
00:19:25.100 --> 00:19:26.852
This isn't for either of you.

269
00:19:28.228 --> 00:19:30.105
Adults can survive on anything.

270
00:19:33.400 --> 00:19:34.568
[grunts wearily]

271
00:19:35.777 --> 00:19:37.863
Use it to make
gruel for the baby.

272
00:19:38.947 --> 00:19:39.948
Ah. well.

273
00:19:40.866 --> 00:19:43.202
there goes all of my
prized white rice.

274
00:19:44.578 --> 00:19:46.455
Pains in the neck. those two.

275
00:19:53.670 --> 00:19:55.631
[Shikishima breathing
heavily. grunts]

276
00:19:58.258 --> 00:20:00.051
Argh. Damn it.

277
00:20:00.052 --> 00:20:01.720
It's pouring out there.

278
00:20:03.180 --> 00:20:04.348
I'm soaked.

279
00:20:08.685 --> 00:20:10.394
Did you find any work?

280
00:20:10.395 --> 00:20:12.730
[Shikishima] Well. actually.

281
00:20:12.731 --> 00:20:14.191
I did find something. but...

282
00:20:14.942 --> 00:20:16.235
Well. that's good news.

283
00:20:17.819 --> 00:20:19.904
[Shikishima] The
money's not bad either.

284
00:20:19.905 --> 00:20:21.073
Here. look.

285
00:20:21.782 --> 00:20:24.325
See what it says? There's
an advance of 3.000 yen.

286
00:20:24.326 --> 00:20:26.036
That's great. isn't it?

287
00:20:30.874 --> 00:20:32.541
It can't be real though.

288
00:20:32.542 --> 00:20:35.795
You remember that other job
where all our rice got stolen?

289
00:20:35.796 --> 00:20:38.422
It's not like that. Things
are different this time.

290
00:20:38.423 --> 00:20:40.424
How can you know
that for sure though?

291
00:20:40.425 --> 00:20:43.302
'Cause this one's got the
government backing it.

292
00:20:43.303 --> 00:20:45.722
And it pays this well
for a good reason.

293
00:20:46.515 --> 00:20:47.682
What reason?

294
00:20:47.683 --> 00:20:48.892
During the war.

295
00:20:49.893 --> 00:20:52.853
both the US and Imperial
navies laid thousands of mines.

296
00:20:52.854 --> 00:20:55.649
and... they need us
to clear them out.

297
00:20:57.693 --> 00:21:00.946
They're offering so
much money... because...

298
00:21:03.991 --> 00:21:07.995
this work. it carries
a certain kind of risk.

299
00:21:10.038 --> 00:21:11.539
Listen to what you're saying!

300
00:21:11.540 --> 00:21:13.416
You can't do this! You
just survived a war!

301
00:21:13.417 --> 00:21:15.251
It's not exactly a choice!

302
00:21:15.252 --> 00:21:17.837
We won't make it if
something doesn't change.

303
00:21:17.838 --> 00:21:19.464
Akiko will starve to death.

304
00:21:20.674 --> 00:21:24.303
I understand that. but...
I can't let you go.

305
00:21:25.387 --> 00:21:27.931
[Shikishima] Look.
this'll bring in money.

306
00:21:28.724 --> 00:21:31.309
And with it. we can buy
American powdered milk

307
00:21:31.310 --> 00:21:33.687
or anything else. If
that means that I...

308
00:21:34.688 --> 00:21:36.773
I can't let that happen to you!

309
00:21:40.986 --> 00:21:42.029
Listen to me.

310
00:21:42.863 --> 00:21:45.991
Just 'cause this is risky. it
doesn't mean that I'll die.

311
00:21:47.367 --> 00:21:49.745
This isn't like the
war. It's not hopeless.

312
00:21:54.708 --> 00:21:57.168
Anyway. they said they use boats

313
00:21:57.169 --> 00:21:59.963
that are specially made
to evade magnetic mines.

314
00:22:04.593 --> 00:22:07.887
This is it? This
is specially made?

315
00:22:07.888 --> 00:22:09.264
[boat creaking]

316
00:22:21.943 --> 00:22:24.653
Hey there. Are you
our new sharpshooter?

317
00:22:24.654 --> 00:22:25.654
Shikishima. yes.

318
00:22:25.655 --> 00:22:26.573
Ex-Navy. huh?

319
00:22:26.574 --> 00:22:27.907
I flew a fighter. actually.

320
00:22:27.908 --> 00:22:30.284
What the hell? What do
we do with this guy?

321
00:22:30.285 --> 00:22:31.869
An airman? You saw
action. didn't you?

322
00:22:31.870 --> 00:22:34.872
He's a military castoff.
Not worth anything to us.

323
00:22:34.873 --> 00:22:36.291
Are you disappointed

324
00:22:37.125 --> 00:22:39.252
that we're using this
old thing? [chuckles]

325
00:22:39.836 --> 00:22:41.045
Well. during the war.

326
00:22:41.046 --> 00:22:44.590
the US and Imperial navies laid
nearly 60.000 mines of all sorts

327
00:22:44.591 --> 00:22:46.050
off the coasts of Japan.

328
00:22:46.051 --> 00:22:49.012
but the ones that worry us are
the American magnetic kind.

329
00:22:49.554 --> 00:22:52.181
If a vessel made out of
metal goes anywhere near one.

330
00:22:52.182 --> 00:22:53.392
a blast is triggered.

331
00:22:55.352 --> 00:22:57.520
Ah. Hence. the wood.

332
00:22:57.521 --> 00:22:59.773
Mm. You catch on pretty quick.

333
00:23:00.440 --> 00:23:03.317
Most of what we can handle
are the standard moored mines.

334
00:23:03.318 --> 00:23:06.822
But with the magnetic ones. wooden
boats are the best countermeasure.

335
00:23:09.324 --> 00:23:10.492
Noda's the name.

336
00:23:11.743 --> 00:23:15.121
During the war. I worked for a while
designing weapons for the navy.

337
00:23:15.122 --> 00:23:17.790
That's our captain. Akitsu.
and that's Mizushima there.

338
00:23:17.791 --> 00:23:19.458
You can call this one
"Kid." He's "Doc."

339
00:23:19.459 --> 00:23:21.877
I'm not very fond of that
nickname. and you know that.

340
00:23:21.878 --> 00:23:23.712
And I'm way too
old for "kid" now.

341
00:23:23.713 --> 00:23:26.298
Sure. but seeing as you're the
greenest one. you're still "Kid."

342
00:23:26.299 --> 00:23:29.552
Yeah. I know. I didn't get to fight
in the war like you. I was too young.

343
00:23:29.553 --> 00:23:32.138
Our minesweeper here is
called the Shinseimaru.

344
00:23:32.139 --> 00:23:34.432
That's the Kaishinmaru
parked there.

345
00:23:34.433 --> 00:23:38.979
The mines we're after are tethered to
the seabed like balloons on strings.

346
00:23:39.521 --> 00:23:43.732
So we run a cable between our two
boats with a cutter in the middle.

347
00:23:43.733 --> 00:23:46.110
All we have to do
is clip the tether.

348
00:23:46.111 --> 00:23:48.571
and the mine floats
to the surface.

349
00:23:48.572 --> 00:23:50.115
Then we hit it with this.

350
00:23:51.450 --> 00:23:53.076
Da-da-da-da-da-dada!

351
00:23:54.077 --> 00:23:55.162
Let me show you.

352
00:24:05.714 --> 00:24:08.467
[grunts] This one's a
little bit squirrelly.

353
00:24:09.259 --> 00:24:10.469
Could you let me try?

354
00:24:11.303 --> 00:24:12.679
Think you can handle her?

355
00:24:14.097 --> 00:24:15.097
Here.

356
00:24:17.559 --> 00:24:19.351
Since we're rocking like this.

357
00:24:19.352 --> 00:24:22.898
I'm trying to account for how the
waves are also moving the target.

358
00:24:29.905 --> 00:24:31.197
Whoa-oh!

359
00:24:31.198 --> 00:24:32.698
[chuckling gleefully]

360
00:24:32.699 --> 00:24:34.034
Nice one!

361
00:24:34.534 --> 00:24:36.410
I learned how to
shoot down fighters.

362
00:24:36.411 --> 00:24:38.871
But I never saw real
action. just simulations.

363
00:24:38.872 --> 00:24:39.872
[Mizushima] What?

364
00:24:40.749 --> 00:24:42.542
You never saw any real action?

365
00:24:43.043 --> 00:24:45.377
I guess Shikishima is
just as green as me. huh?

366
00:24:45.378 --> 00:24:48.172
Learn how to fly a plane like
he can. then we can talk.

367
00:24:48.173 --> 00:24:51.175
If I'd fought in the war. I
know I'd have been useful too.

368
00:24:51.176 --> 00:24:53.970
Ah. if only it had
just kept on going.

369
00:24:56.640 --> 00:24:59.184
Don't say anything
like that ever again.

370
00:25:01.019 --> 00:25:03.188
[chuckles nervously]
It was just a joke.

371
00:25:07.150 --> 00:25:08.568
Use your brain. Kid.

372
00:25:14.449 --> 00:25:15.867
[thundering footstep]

373
00:25:21.081 --> 00:25:22.165
[thundering footstep]

374
00:25:23.917 --> 00:25:25.418
[unsettling music playing]

375
00:25:28.088 --> 00:25:29.172
[thundering footstep]

376
00:25:32.133 --> 00:25:33.176
[Shikishima gasps]

377
00:25:34.094 --> 00:25:35.970
- [panicked shouting]
- We have to stop it!

378
00:25:35.971 --> 00:25:38.639
- [mechanics yelping]
- [man 1] Fire! Shoot it. guys! Shoot it!

379
00:25:38.640 --> 00:25:41.351
Fire! Fall back! Go! Go!

380
00:25:41.893 --> 00:25:43.227
[man 2 screams]

381
00:25:43.228 --> 00:25:44.646
[ominous music playing]

382
00:25:47.649 --> 00:25:48.984
[Godzilla snarling softly]

383
00:25:49.609 --> 00:25:50.985
[roaring]

384
00:25:50.986 --> 00:25:53.112
- [growling]
- [Shikishima whimpering]

385
00:25:53.113 --> 00:25:54.905
[screaming]

386
00:25:54.906 --> 00:25:56.658
[gasps. panting]

387
00:25:59.160 --> 00:26:00.161
You all right?

388
00:26:01.705 --> 00:26:02.705
Oh.

389
00:26:07.836 --> 00:26:09.045
Another nightmare?

390
00:26:17.387 --> 00:26:18.387
Nightmare?

391
00:26:22.183 --> 00:26:23.184
That's right.

392
00:26:24.853 --> 00:26:26.521
I was dreaming.

393
00:26:34.195 --> 00:26:35.195
What if

394
00:26:36.781 --> 00:26:38.950
you here. that's the dream?

395
00:26:39.659 --> 00:26:42.202
- I don't understand you. Are you sure...
- Is this...?

396
00:26:42.203 --> 00:26:44.079
We're in Japan. right? Right?

397
00:26:44.080 --> 00:26:46.915
I... I made it back alive.
I came back. right? Right?!

398
00:26:46.916 --> 00:26:49.711
- I... I made it back alive. right?
- Get off! [grunts]

399
00:26:51.171 --> 00:26:52.922
[panting]

400
00:27:10.357 --> 00:27:11.441
Right. I know.

401
00:27:12.192 --> 00:27:14.027
I know. [sobbing]

402
00:27:15.445 --> 00:27:16.696
I know.

403
00:27:20.158 --> 00:27:23.077
[explosion reverberating]

404
00:27:23.078 --> 00:27:24.913
[Godzilla snarling]

405
00:27:25.497 --> 00:27:27.540
[Godzilla screeching painfully]

406
00:27:33.088 --> 00:27:34.631
[idyllic music playing]

407
00:27:39.678 --> 00:27:41.304
[inaudible]

408
00:27:48.520 --> 00:27:51.815
[inaudible]

409
00:27:53.566 --> 00:27:55.151
[idyllic music continues]

410
00:28:01.950 --> 00:28:04.244
- [idyllic music continues]
- [inaudible]

411
00:28:23.430 --> 00:28:26.890
[Akitsu] You've built a real nice
place. It's worth every penny saved.

412
00:28:26.891 --> 00:28:27.891
SHIKISHIMA

413
00:28:27.892 --> 00:28:29.601
[laughter]

414
00:28:29.602 --> 00:28:31.228
- [Shikishima] Mmm.
- [Mizushima] Mmm.

415
00:28:31.229 --> 00:28:32.355
[chuckling]

416
00:28:33.106 --> 00:28:34.440
Would you like some more?

417
00:28:34.441 --> 00:28:36.693
Ah. Yes. please. Thanks.

418
00:28:38.945 --> 00:28:41.488
Uh. how about a
photo. huh? [chuckles]

419
00:28:41.489 --> 00:28:44.575
[chuckles] Oh no. please.
don't waste your film on me.

420
00:28:44.576 --> 00:28:47.077
- [all chuckling]
- Look at that smile! Hold it!

421
00:28:47.078 --> 00:28:48.412
- Hold it.
- [Mizushima] Very nice.

422
00:28:48.413 --> 00:28:50.123
- [Noda] And...
- [shutter clicks]

423
00:28:51.124 --> 00:28:52.124
- Ah!
- [chuckling]

424
00:28:52.125 --> 00:28:53.751
- [Noriko] Thank you.
- Watch out. Doc.

425
00:28:53.752 --> 00:28:55.961
- Don't go falling for Noriko.
- [Mizushima] He's right.

426
00:28:55.962 --> 00:28:59.381
You shouldn't joke like that.
Noriko's a married woman. [chuckles]

427
00:28:59.382 --> 00:29:01.425
Everyone. please. that's enough!

428
00:29:01.426 --> 00:29:02.802
I'm not his wife.

429
00:29:06.681 --> 00:29:07.682
She's not?

430
00:29:08.600 --> 00:29:10.351
Yeah. she just
showed up one day.

431
00:29:11.102 --> 00:29:14.230
She had nowhere else to
go. so I let her stay.

432
00:29:14.981 --> 00:29:16.190
And the little girl?

433
00:29:16.191 --> 00:29:17.900
She brought Akiko with her.

434
00:29:17.901 --> 00:29:20.444
But they're not related
to each other. Not really.

435
00:29:20.445 --> 00:29:23.989
She was an orphan that Noriko
took in during the air raids.

436
00:29:23.990 --> 00:29:24.990
[Noda] Oh.

437
00:29:25.825 --> 00:29:28.368
You all found each other.
What a lovely story.

438
00:29:28.369 --> 00:29:31.039
[chuckles awkwardly] That's
just sort of how it went.

439
00:29:33.583 --> 00:29:34.584
Daddy.

440
00:29:36.961 --> 00:29:38.588
- Akiko.
- [Akiko] Mm?

441
00:29:40.089 --> 00:29:42.759
I told you. You know
I'm not your father.

442
00:29:45.094 --> 00:29:46.387
Oh. Shikishima!

443
00:29:47.055 --> 00:29:49.849
- That's awful. How could you say that?
- What a hurtful thing to say.

444
00:29:50.975 --> 00:29:54.521
Here's the thing. fate has
brought you together as a family.

445
00:29:55.146 --> 00:29:56.897
You need to find a
way to accept that.

446
00:29:56.898 --> 00:29:59.274
That's right. Now I need a hug!

447
00:29:59.275 --> 00:30:00.400
[laughter]

448
00:30:00.401 --> 00:30:01.694
- Yeah.
- That's enough!

449
00:30:02.529 --> 00:30:03.738
I don't want that.

450
00:30:06.699 --> 00:30:07.699
[sighs]

451
00:30:09.994 --> 00:30:10.995
[Akitsu] Why not?

452
00:30:17.585 --> 00:30:19.170
[motorcycle approaching]

453
00:30:26.719 --> 00:30:29.514
[Noriko] Welcome home.
I just got back myself.

454
00:30:30.348 --> 00:30:32.183
What are those
clothes you have on?

455
00:30:35.186 --> 00:30:36.396
How do I look?

456
00:30:37.272 --> 00:30:39.231
I went to Ginza and
found myself a job.

457
00:30:39.232 --> 00:30:42.485
Uh. well. is this 'cause I
don't provide enough for you?

458
00:30:48.449 --> 00:30:51.327
It's not that. I just always
wanted to be self-sufficient.

459
00:30:52.704 --> 00:30:55.707
And you'll never find a
wife if I'm always around.

460
00:31:00.086 --> 00:31:01.169
And besides.

461
00:31:01.170 --> 00:31:03.506
Ginza's come such a
long way since the war.

462
00:31:04.299 --> 00:31:05.675
This feels so sudden.

463
00:31:06.801 --> 00:31:08.303
I don't really think it is.

464
00:31:09.554 --> 00:31:10.805
Well. Akiko!

465
00:31:11.306 --> 00:31:13.599
Uh. what will Akiko do?

466
00:31:13.600 --> 00:31:17.687
Who's going to be here to look after
her while you go work in Ginza?

467
00:31:18.438 --> 00:31:21.316
We talked. and Sumiko said
she'd be happy to watch her.

468
00:31:22.400 --> 00:31:24.860
- Oh.
- She seemed very excited.

469
00:31:24.861 --> 00:31:28.323
She said. "I've already raised
three. Why not?" [chuckles]

470
00:31:29.741 --> 00:31:31.159
Oh. I see.

471
00:31:31.826 --> 00:31:33.536
Well. all right. then.

472
00:31:35.038 --> 00:31:37.206
Good. I'll go get Akiko.

473
00:31:46.132 --> 00:31:47.467
[sighs]

474
00:31:48.843 --> 00:31:49.761
[projector whirs]

475
00:31:49.762 --> 00:31:51.970
[man 1] <i>Pacific Fleet
Destroyer USS Lancaster</i>

476
00:31:51.971 --> 00:31:54.264
<i>was attacked and disabled
by an unknown enemy.</i>

477
00:31:54.265 --> 00:31:56.351
<i>No further details
known at this time.</i>

478
00:31:56.851 --> 00:32:00.729
<i>Intercepted urgent distress call from
Pacific Fleet attack sub USS Redfish.</i>

479
00:32:00.730 --> 00:32:02.773
<i>reporting pursuit of
massive undersea organism</i>

480
00:32:02.774 --> 00:32:04.191
<i>through Pacific waters.</i>

481
00:32:04.192 --> 00:32:06.276
<i>After successfully
photographing target.</i>

482
00:32:06.277 --> 00:32:08.695
<i>Redfish made contact
and was destroyed.</i>

483
00:32:08.696 --> 00:32:11.448
<i>Wreck reconnaissance picked
up radio-isotope emissions</i>

484
00:32:11.449 --> 00:32:13.785
<i>where hull collided with
enemy creature skin.</i>

485
00:32:18.873 --> 00:32:20.791
[man 2] <i>The colossal sea
creature is projected</i>

486
00:32:20.792 --> 00:32:23.502
<i>to reach the Japanese
archipelago within a few weeks.</i>

487
00:32:23.503 --> 00:32:27.464
<i>Its recorded movement suggests a course
to the Kanto region specifically.</i>

488
00:32:27.465 --> 00:32:29.299
[warning beacon beeping]

489
00:32:29.300 --> 00:32:32.844
[man 2] <i>General Douglas MacArthur
commented on the developing situation.</i>

490
00:32:32.845 --> 00:32:34.304
<i>stating with regret</i>

491
00:32:34.305 --> 00:32:38.600
<i>that recent Soviet movements
prevent any US military assistance.</i>

492
00:32:38.601 --> 00:32:42.312
<i>He instead calls on Japan to begin
strengthening its own security forces</i>

493
00:32:42.313 --> 00:32:45.315
<i>in preparation for potential
contact with the beast.</i>

494
00:32:45.316 --> 00:32:46.817
[projector whirs]

495
00:32:46.818 --> 00:32:48.903
[foreboding music playing]

496
00:32:58.538 --> 00:33:00.164
[Akitsu] What could do this?

497
00:33:01.040 --> 00:33:02.333
Some kind of whale?

498
00:33:04.002 --> 00:33:05.335
Or giant shark?

499
00:33:05.336 --> 00:33:08.506
Shark or whale couldn't do that.
No. this is something else.

500
00:33:09.507 --> 00:33:13.093
- [Mizushima] Maybe a new Soviet weapon?
- [Noda] Does that look like weapon damage?

501
00:33:13.094 --> 00:33:14.721
Then what else could it be?

502
00:33:15.513 --> 00:33:17.556
My guess would be an
enormous creature.

503
00:33:17.557 --> 00:33:21.184
Oh. come on. Your crazy theories
aren't any better than ours.

504
00:33:21.185 --> 00:33:24.313
I was skeptical until I
got a closer look at this.

505
00:33:26.941 --> 00:33:27.941
Godzilla.

506
00:33:29.569 --> 00:33:31.695
Uh... Look! Starboard side!

507
00:33:31.696 --> 00:33:33.072
[Akitsu] Huh?

508
00:33:33.656 --> 00:33:34.699
[Noda] Huh?

509
00:33:35.283 --> 00:33:37.617
[Shikishima] I saw deep sea
fish floating just like this

510
00:33:37.618 --> 00:33:39.536
the day a monster
attacked Odo island.

511
00:33:39.537 --> 00:33:42.205
A monster? Like what?

512
00:33:42.206 --> 00:33:43.749
It was like a dinosaur

513
00:33:43.750 --> 00:33:46.502
that. over the years. had
turned into something else.

514
00:33:47.045 --> 00:33:50.798
I remember hearing that the
locals called it Godzilla.

515
00:33:51.632 --> 00:33:52.467
Godzilla?

516
00:33:52.468 --> 00:33:56.636
Come on. Don't be ridiculous. I
bet you just saw a tank that you...

517
00:33:56.637 --> 00:33:58.346
You can believe me or not.

518
00:33:58.347 --> 00:34:00.057
It still doesn't change the fact

519
00:34:00.058 --> 00:34:03.519
that Godzilla wiped out
everyone on Odo Island.

520
00:34:04.103 --> 00:34:05.104
Wait a minute.

521
00:34:06.022 --> 00:34:08.357
I thought the Americans
took out that garrison.

522
00:34:10.234 --> 00:34:13.696
[Shikishima] The US island-hopping
forces never targeted Odo.

523
00:34:14.280 --> 00:34:18.159
At that point. it was only being used
as a repair base for kamikaze planes.

524
00:34:18.826 --> 00:34:20.244
Wait. Shikishima.

525
00:34:21.662 --> 00:34:23.456
Does that mean you
were a kamikaze pilot?

526
00:34:29.545 --> 00:34:32.423
[Shikishima] If this is the
same Godzilla I saw back then.

527
00:34:33.257 --> 00:34:36.719
and it can do this. then
it's even bigger than before.

528
00:34:39.430 --> 00:34:41.349
[Mizushima giggles nervously]

529
00:34:42.767 --> 00:34:44.352
Just hold on a second.

530
00:34:44.936 --> 00:34:48.314
Why are we here? I don't see how
the four of us can do anything.

531
00:34:49.190 --> 00:34:50.233
I mean. how...

532
00:34:50.817 --> 00:34:53.485
They don't honestly expect us
to fight that thing in this.

533
00:34:53.486 --> 00:34:54.779
They obviously do.

534
00:34:55.321 --> 00:34:58.615
[Mizushima] What? We don't stand
a chance! Not against that!

535
00:34:58.616 --> 00:35:00.826
A big US cruiser
couldn't take it down.

536
00:35:00.827 --> 00:35:03.370
We're a couple of planks of wood.
How are we gonna do anything?!

537
00:35:03.371 --> 00:35:05.206
We can distract it for a while.

538
00:35:06.415 --> 00:35:07.416
Are you joking?

539
00:35:07.959 --> 00:35:10.711
Singapore's sending us the
Takao from their docks.

540
00:35:11.504 --> 00:35:13.547
Huh? Wait. As in
the heavy cruiser?

541
00:35:13.548 --> 00:35:17.009
Instead of scuttling it there.
they're going to let us use it again.

542
00:35:17.802 --> 00:35:20.387
Well. then. that's
great! The Takao is huge!

543
00:35:20.388 --> 00:35:24.224
Our orders are to do whatever it takes
to stall for time until it gets here.

544
00:35:24.225 --> 00:35:27.603
That's an American destroyer. How
come they can't deal with this?

545
00:35:28.688 --> 00:35:31.982
I wouldn't count on it. It's about
enough of the Soviets as it is.

546
00:35:31.983 --> 00:35:35.027
The US risks furthering those
tensions if they do anything.

547
00:35:35.528 --> 00:35:38.697
For little things like this. they'd
rather us handle it on our own.

548
00:35:38.698 --> 00:35:40.240
I wouldn't call this little.

549
00:35:40.241 --> 00:35:42.576
And plus. all we've
got is a 13 mm gun.

550
00:35:42.577 --> 00:35:46.205
Which is exactly why they said we
should use a few mines we've recovered.

551
00:35:46.831 --> 00:35:51.168
Aha! That's why we're the
ones that got called out here.

552
00:35:51.169 --> 00:35:52.128
Of course.

553
00:35:52.129 --> 00:35:55.463
They needed a team that could
scavenge their own weapons locally.

554
00:35:55.464 --> 00:35:59.634
They also ordered us not to tell anyone
about the creature or what we're doing.

555
00:35:59.635 --> 00:36:03.139
[Akitsu] And there it is.
Their favorite. the gag order.

556
00:36:04.432 --> 00:36:06.142
This country never changes.

557
00:36:07.602 --> 00:36:08.811
I wonder if it can.

558
00:36:18.487 --> 00:36:20.907
All right. it's my turn. Here.

559
00:36:22.658 --> 00:36:23.659
Thank you.

560
00:36:24.660 --> 00:36:27.163
Try not to push yourself
too hard. Shiki-san.

561
00:36:27.705 --> 00:36:30.666
I know. I can't help it if
this really is Godzilla.

562
00:36:32.460 --> 00:36:33.628
I know the feeling.

563
00:36:34.503 --> 00:36:37.423
When I think about the things
that happened in the war.

564
00:36:38.466 --> 00:36:40.176
I have a hard time sleeping.

565
00:36:41.636 --> 00:36:43.012
I have to avenge them.

566
00:36:43.930 --> 00:36:45.181
But then I remember

567
00:36:46.474 --> 00:36:48.517
how terrifying that thing was.

568
00:36:54.774 --> 00:36:58.611
We only have a pair of those.
one of which is for an emergency.

569
00:37:00.655 --> 00:37:02.406
[water plopping]

570
00:37:04.575 --> 00:37:05.993
Oh. What's the matter?

571
00:37:07.119 --> 00:37:09.372
[water plopping]

572
00:37:24.095 --> 00:37:25.346
Look at that.

573
00:37:26.055 --> 00:37:28.724
There's way more fish than
there was back on Odo.

574
00:37:29.600 --> 00:37:31.435
[breathing rapidly]

575
00:37:31.936 --> 00:37:34.105
Sound the alarm!
Sound the alarm!

576
00:37:34.689 --> 00:37:36.147
Godzilla's gotta be close!

577
00:37:36.148 --> 00:37:37.775
Sound the alarm!

578
00:37:39.610 --> 00:37:41.237
[Akitsu] So it's coming. huh?

579
00:37:42.113 --> 00:37:44.572
Hey. Kid! Get ready to drop
those mines in. all right?

580
00:37:44.573 --> 00:37:46.491
- [Mizushima] Roger!
- Shikishima! Get on the gun!

581
00:37:46.492 --> 00:37:49.286
We should retreat. We don't stand
a chance fighting it like this.

582
00:37:49.287 --> 00:37:51.955
- If we leave now. we'll make it.
- We should see how it acts first.

583
00:37:51.956 --> 00:37:53.957
Doc. go stand aft and
call out anything you see.

584
00:37:53.958 --> 00:37:56.669
- Captain. please!
- Hey. Kaishinmaru. You fellas copy?

585
00:37:57.169 --> 00:38:00.130
They say it's gonna show soon.
Get ready to land the big one.

586
00:38:00.131 --> 00:38:03.216
[man on radio] <i>Roger that. Hope you
don't mind us taking the credit.</i>

587
00:38:03.217 --> 00:38:04.592
- Like hell.
- We need to go!

588
00:38:04.593 --> 00:38:07.470
If we run now. the Takao
won't make it in time.

589
00:38:07.471 --> 00:38:10.182
After that. where do you
think this thing's gonna go?

590
00:38:11.350 --> 00:38:14.060
I don't wanna see Tokyo
in a sea of fire again.

591
00:38:14.061 --> 00:38:16.479
Listen. There's no way
our ship can handle it!

592
00:38:16.480 --> 00:38:19.232
I thought you said you hated the
government telling you what to do!

593
00:38:19.233 --> 00:38:21.068
Yeah. this doesn't change that!

594
00:38:21.610 --> 00:38:22.611
The thing is.

595
00:38:23.362 --> 00:38:25.573
if we don't step up.
who the hell's going to?

596
00:38:27.074 --> 00:38:28.868
[booming in distance]

597
00:38:29.869 --> 00:38:30.995
[alarms sounding]

598
00:38:31.954 --> 00:38:33.664
[men screaming]

599
00:38:37.209 --> 00:38:38.961
[breathing heavily]

600
00:38:42.506 --> 00:38:44.800
Actually. let the
Takao handle this one.

601
00:38:49.305 --> 00:38:50.638
Hey. Doc. the engine!

602
00:38:50.639 --> 00:38:52.016
I'm doing my best!

603
00:38:52.641 --> 00:38:53.893
[Mizushima] Shikishima!

604
00:38:55.478 --> 00:38:56.936
- Shikishima!
- Coming!

605
00:38:56.937 --> 00:38:58.939
[Mizushima] Hurry!
Help me with this!

606
00:39:00.900 --> 00:39:03.360
- Captain!
- [Akitsu] Yeah. I see it!

607
00:39:03.361 --> 00:39:05.362
- Full throttle ahead!
- Got it!

608
00:39:05.363 --> 00:39:06.280
[grunts]

609
00:39:06.281 --> 00:39:07.448
[engine chugging]

610
00:39:16.540 --> 00:39:18.501
[Mizushima grunting]

611
00:39:26.175 --> 00:39:27.968
Get it in the water. now!

612
00:39:29.136 --> 00:39:31.012
It's too close. There's
no way we'll make it!

613
00:39:31.013 --> 00:39:33.224
Just drop the goddamn mine. Doc!

614
00:39:34.100 --> 00:39:36.185
[strained grunting]

615
00:39:37.144 --> 00:39:39.146
[tense suspenseful
music playing]

616
00:39:45.152 --> 00:39:46.945
[all panting]

617
00:39:46.946 --> 00:39:48.114
[gasps]

618
00:39:51.367 --> 00:39:52.742
[Godzilla rumbling]

619
00:39:52.743 --> 00:39:54.202
All right. Kid! Hit it!

620
00:39:54.203 --> 00:39:56.122
Blowing the mine! [grunts]

621
00:39:59.500 --> 00:40:00.793
[all yelp]

622
00:40:01.919 --> 00:40:03.087
Is it dead?

623
00:40:06.340 --> 00:40:08.425
[Godzilla growling angrily]

624
00:40:08.426 --> 00:40:10.802
It's still on our tail!

625
00:40:10.803 --> 00:40:13.179
Oh man. oh man. oh man.
oh man! I'm gonna die!

626
00:40:13.180 --> 00:40:15.014
Shikishima. the gun!

627
00:40:15.015 --> 00:40:16.558
- Roger!
- [Mizushima whimpers]

628
00:40:16.559 --> 00:40:19.060
[Godzilla snarling]

629
00:40:19.061 --> 00:40:20.228
[grunts]

630
00:40:20.229 --> 00:40:21.730
[breathing shakily]

631
00:40:23.858 --> 00:40:25.234
Shikishima!

632
00:40:27.653 --> 00:40:28.736
- [grunting]
- [gunfire]

633
00:40:28.737 --> 00:40:30.573
[Shikishima yelling]

634
00:40:36.203 --> 00:40:38.288
Damn it! It didn't do anything!

635
00:40:38.289 --> 00:40:40.207
[Godzilla growling]

636
00:40:42.209 --> 00:40:45.171
I have an idea. What if
we hit it in the mouth?

637
00:40:46.172 --> 00:40:47.297
[Shikishima grunts]

638
00:40:47.298 --> 00:40:50.759
[Noda] Reel. reel. reel! Hurry!
Quick! Get the line ready!

639
00:40:51.760 --> 00:40:53.762
Drop it! [grunting]

640
00:41:00.144 --> 00:41:02.562
Mizushima! Hit the switch!

641
00:41:02.563 --> 00:41:03.522
[yelling]

642
00:41:03.523 --> 00:41:04.940
- [grunts]
- [silence]

643
00:41:05.608 --> 00:41:06.692
[confused grunt]

644
00:41:07.651 --> 00:41:10.196
[Godzilla snarling]

645
00:41:12.490 --> 00:41:13.491
Hey!

646
00:41:14.116 --> 00:41:15.117
What's wrong?

647
00:41:15.743 --> 00:41:16.743
You're kidding!

648
00:41:17.161 --> 00:41:18.746
[Godzilla growling]

649
00:41:27.213 --> 00:41:28.255
[mine clinks]

650
00:41:28.756 --> 00:41:30.549
[Shikishima] You two. get down!

651
00:41:31.634 --> 00:41:34.344
[Shikishima yelling]

652
00:41:34.345 --> 00:41:36.137
[panting]

653
00:41:36.138 --> 00:41:38.807
[gunfire continues]

654
00:41:40.017 --> 00:41:41.101
[Shikishima grunts]

655
00:41:45.606 --> 00:41:48.901
- [yelling]
- [panting]

656
00:41:51.111 --> 00:41:52.111
[gasps]

657
00:41:54.198 --> 00:41:55.616
Did it work. Doc?

658
00:41:58.244 --> 00:41:59.954
[panting]

659
00:42:01.163 --> 00:42:02.498
[flesh squelching]

660
00:42:03.374 --> 00:42:04.625
- [groaning]
- No!

661
00:42:16.011 --> 00:42:17.972
[Mizushima whimpering]

662
00:42:22.851 --> 00:42:24.937
[Godzilla roaring]

663
00:42:25.938 --> 00:42:27.690
[ship horn blaring]

664
00:42:29.692 --> 00:42:32.486
- [Akitsu] It's the Takao!
- [Noda] They made it.

665
00:42:43.455 --> 00:42:45.249
[Noda panting. grunting]

666
00:42:46.041 --> 00:42:48.043
[unsettling music playing]

667
00:43:00.806 --> 00:43:02.266
Wait. What's it doing?

668
00:43:03.601 --> 00:43:06.478
[Godzilla roaring]

669
00:43:07.271 --> 00:43:09.188
[panicked screaming]

670
00:43:09.189 --> 00:43:10.608
[dramatic music playing]

671
00:43:13.944 --> 00:43:15.362
[men screaming]

672
00:43:20.492 --> 00:43:22.328
- [gasping]
- [panicked yelping]

673
00:43:23.120 --> 00:43:24.622
[man 1] Get in the lifeboats!

674
00:43:26.206 --> 00:43:27.333
[Godzilla snarling]

675
00:43:28.250 --> 00:43:29.627
[alarm sounding]

676
00:43:31.420 --> 00:43:33.422
[Godzilla growling]

677
00:43:36.634 --> 00:43:37.718
[screaming]

678
00:43:39.887 --> 00:43:40.888
Did we kill it?

679
00:43:41.388 --> 00:43:43.098
[suspenseful music building]

680
00:43:44.808 --> 00:43:46.477
[Noda breathing heavily]

681
00:43:52.399 --> 00:43:53.399
What's that?

682
00:44:00.866 --> 00:44:02.493
[shocked panting]

683
00:44:05.454 --> 00:44:07.247
[ominous music playing]

684
00:44:12.002 --> 00:44:15.047
[roaring]

685
00:44:16.757 --> 00:44:17.757
[roaring stops]

686
00:44:26.183 --> 00:44:27.309
[music fades]

687
00:44:36.694 --> 00:44:37.902
[groans weakly]

688
00:44:37.903 --> 00:44:39.113
[silence]

689
00:44:49.039 --> 00:44:50.582
[exhales slowly]

690
00:44:54.336 --> 00:44:55.796
Good. You're finally awake.

691
00:44:58.006 --> 00:44:59.007
Where am I?

692
00:44:59.967 --> 00:45:03.178
Yokosuka Hospital. They
rescued us after the attack.

693
00:45:04.847 --> 00:45:07.850
The Kaishinmaru and Takao
crews. did they make it?

694
00:45:13.147 --> 00:45:15.232
Oh. Godzilla...

695
00:45:16.233 --> 00:45:17.233
- That's right.
- Easy.

696
00:45:17.234 --> 00:45:18.901
Where did it go? What happened?

697
00:45:18.902 --> 00:45:21.654
It disappeared. No
one knows where it is.

698
00:45:21.655 --> 00:45:23.823
Godzilla was headed
straight for the mainland.

699
00:45:23.824 --> 00:45:25.950
We need to evacuate everyone.
or this is going to be...

700
00:45:25.951 --> 00:45:29.579
Not so fast. The country has
decided not to tell the public.

701
00:45:29.580 --> 00:45:31.914
Why wouldn't they tell
everyone they're in danger?

702
00:45:31.915 --> 00:45:34.751
{\an8}Because they don't want
things to get out of control.

703
00:45:34.752 --> 00:45:37.044
{\an8}There's no time to
worry about any of that.

704
00:45:37.045 --> 00:45:38.796
{\an8}We need to begin evacuating
now. otherwise...

705
00:45:38.797 --> 00:45:41.550
{\an8}I understand what you're
saying. and I agree with you.

706
00:45:42.176 --> 00:45:43.509
{\an8}But they don't want chaos.

707
00:45:43.510 --> 00:45:46.597
{\an8}Information control is the only
thing this country's good at.

708
00:45:55.522 --> 00:45:57.608
I want to know what's
going on with you.

709
00:45:59.151 --> 00:46:01.820
Noriko. I'm fine. It's got
nothing to do with you.

710
00:46:03.989 --> 00:46:06.450
Tell me what this thing
is that's tormenting you.

711
00:46:09.161 --> 00:46:12.956
Ever since you took me in.
we've built a life together.

712
00:46:13.749 --> 00:46:17.461
But even through all of that. you
never really let me into your life.

713
00:46:24.885 --> 00:46:26.970
I know it has to
be a heavy burden.

714
00:46:28.430 --> 00:46:30.682
I wish you'd let me
help you carry it.

715
00:46:42.611 --> 00:46:43.695
During the war...

716
00:46:46.073 --> 00:46:47.074
I was...

717
00:46:50.994 --> 00:46:52.037
[sighs]

718
00:46:57.543 --> 00:46:58.710
In the war...

719
00:47:03.465 --> 00:47:04.842
I was a kamikaze.

720
00:47:06.552 --> 00:47:07.552
What?

721
00:47:08.178 --> 00:47:09.596
The day I was sent out...

722
00:47:12.599 --> 00:47:15.018
I pretended there was an
issue with my fighter.

723
00:47:17.229 --> 00:47:18.730
So I flew to an island

724
00:47:20.232 --> 00:47:21.608
and landed for repairs.

725
00:47:35.122 --> 00:47:36.206
These photos.

726
00:47:37.916 --> 00:47:41.295
they... they belonged
to the mechanics there.

727
00:47:44.339 --> 00:47:47.175
That day. they all died.

728
00:48:01.607 --> 00:48:02.649
During the night.

729
00:48:04.484 --> 00:48:07.529
a giant monster. like a
dinosaur. came ashore.

730
00:48:11.533 --> 00:48:12.533
They asked me

731
00:48:13.619 --> 00:48:16.121
to shoot at it with
the gun on my fighter.

732
00:48:19.499 --> 00:48:20.584
But I froze.

733
00:48:26.256 --> 00:48:27.549
I just ran away again.

734
00:48:29.676 --> 00:48:32.262
I let them die. It
was all my fault.

735
00:48:33.805 --> 00:48:35.723
I let that thing kill everyone.

736
00:48:35.724 --> 00:48:38.226
They were going to return
home to their families!

737
00:48:43.649 --> 00:48:44.649
The monster...

738
00:48:47.319 --> 00:48:49.112
Godzilla. that was its name.

739
00:48:53.742 --> 00:48:56.411
The other day. I saw it again.

740
00:48:59.456 --> 00:49:00.958
And just like back then...

741
00:49:03.669 --> 00:49:05.462
I couldn't do
anything to stop it.

742
00:49:08.382 --> 00:49:09.382
[breathing shakily]

743
00:49:15.472 --> 00:49:16.848
I don't deserve this.

744
00:49:18.934 --> 00:49:20.811
Why should I get
the chance to live?

745
00:49:27.818 --> 00:49:28.902
Koichi.

746
00:49:31.655 --> 00:49:35.866
Everyone who survived the war. they
all deserve to have a life again.

747
00:49:35.867 --> 00:49:37.827
Oh yeah? And how
would you know that?

748
00:49:37.828 --> 00:49:39.079
Because of my parents!

749
00:49:40.122 --> 00:49:43.917
As they died in the fire. they called
out and said they wanted me to live.

750
00:49:44.793 --> 00:49:48.630
Whatever happens. whatever I do.
I know that I have to survive.

751
00:49:50.257 --> 00:49:52.009
It's what keeps me going.

752
00:50:04.396 --> 00:50:05.396
I can't.

753
00:50:05.397 --> 00:50:07.149
[shuddering breaths]

754
00:50:08.567 --> 00:50:12.029
Every night. I hear them
calling to me in my dreams.

755
00:50:12.946 --> 00:50:14.906
"Come and join us
already." they say.

756
00:50:15.699 --> 00:50:18.702
"Stop trying to cheat death
and accept your fate."

757
00:50:19.202 --> 00:50:22.997
Those are just nightmares. Illusions
that you created for yourself...

758
00:50:22.998 --> 00:50:25.333
Sometimes...
sometimes I wonder...

759
00:50:26.668 --> 00:50:29.254
I wonder... if I'm still alive.

760
00:50:31.715 --> 00:50:33.467
What if I did die
on that island.

761
00:50:34.176 --> 00:50:35.427
and I'm rotting there?

762
00:50:36.428 --> 00:50:39.305
You... What if you and Akiko...

763
00:50:39.306 --> 00:50:43.142
What if the two of you are just
the final dreams of a dead man?

764
00:50:43.143 --> 00:50:45.394
That's it! It has
to be! I know it!

765
00:50:45.395 --> 00:50:47.564
- You are alive!
- [sobbing]

766
00:50:51.485 --> 00:50:54.112
- You're alive. Koichi.
- [sobbing]

767
00:50:57.574 --> 00:50:59.034
Why can't you feel that?

768
00:51:00.327 --> 00:51:02.120
[Shikishima sobbing]

769
00:51:13.215 --> 00:51:15.759
[Noriko] Okay. Hold the spoon.

770
00:51:16.676 --> 00:51:19.262
See. Gently. gently.

771
00:51:20.013 --> 00:51:21.973
- Be patient.
- [Akiko] Okay.

772
00:51:22.974 --> 00:51:25.643
- [Noriko] Good. Now stir the broth.
- [Akiko] Mm-hmm.

773
00:51:25.644 --> 00:51:27.145
[Noriko] You're doing great.

774
00:51:28.480 --> 00:51:31.358
- There. it's done!
- [Akiko] Yay!

775
00:51:32.651 --> 00:51:35.194
And look. I added
your favorite. daikon.

776
00:51:35.195 --> 00:51:37.571
- [Akiko] Daikon!
- Let me know how it tastes.

777
00:51:37.572 --> 00:51:39.825
- [Akiko] Okay.
- You ready for a sip?

778
00:51:42.202 --> 00:51:44.746
First the soup. then the daikon.

779
00:51:46.373 --> 00:51:48.333
- [Akiko] I like it.
- [Noriko] Is it hot?

780
00:51:48.917 --> 00:51:50.919
- Don't burn your tongue.
- [Akiko] Mm-hmm.

781
00:51:51.837 --> 00:51:53.796
[Noriko] Have another
bite. How is it?

782
00:51:53.797 --> 00:51:55.297
- [Akiko] Mmm!
- [Noriko chuckles]

783
00:51:55.298 --> 00:51:57.341
- [Akiko] It's yummy.
- [Noriko] You like it?

784
00:51:57.342 --> 00:51:58.552
Am I really...

785
00:52:00.971 --> 00:52:02.764
allowed to dream again now?

786
00:52:09.938 --> 00:52:11.815
Can I finally live my life?

787
00:52:24.786 --> 00:52:26.120
[unsettling music playing]

788
00:52:26.121 --> 00:52:27.706
[startled gasping]

789
00:52:30.959 --> 00:52:33.378
Whoa. Is that it?

790
00:52:34.588 --> 00:52:36.173
Hey. Go call it in.

791
00:52:37.591 --> 00:52:40.135
- Hurry! Go!
- Yes. sir!

792
00:52:44.097 --> 00:52:45.807
[tense music playing]

793
00:53:00.989 --> 00:53:02.907
We just heard from
an offshore patrol.

794
00:53:02.908 --> 00:53:05.452
A giant creature is
heading toward Tokyo Bay.

795
00:53:06.036 --> 00:53:07.704
Then it should be here soon.

796
00:53:09.039 --> 00:53:10.873
- [gasps]
- [man 1] What is it?

797
00:53:10.874 --> 00:53:13.210
- I don't believe it.
- You see something?

798
00:53:13.835 --> 00:53:16.588
Look at it. Have you ever
seen anything like that?

799
00:53:18.381 --> 00:53:21.300
This is Tokyo Bay Defense.
Preparing to detonate zone four.

800
00:53:21.301 --> 00:53:24.094
We'll try to block the creature
from going any further.

801
00:53:24.095 --> 00:53:26.181
It's closing in. Almost there!

802
00:53:27.766 --> 00:53:29.267
[unsettling music playing]

803
00:53:30.393 --> 00:53:31.937
Breaching zone four now!

804
00:53:33.104 --> 00:53:34.522
- There it is!
- Detonate!

805
00:53:37.776 --> 00:53:38.776
That get it?

806
00:53:39.819 --> 00:53:42.197
No good. The mines
didn't damage it!

807
00:53:42.948 --> 00:53:44.448
Tokyo Bay blockade breached!

808
00:53:44.449 --> 00:53:46.450
The monster is now
heading towards Shinagawa!

809
00:53:46.451 --> 00:53:48.536
And it's gargantuan!

810
00:53:49.913 --> 00:53:51.121
[Godzilla growls softly]

811
00:53:51.122 --> 00:53:53.166
- Oh. Oh!
- [jaunty music playing]

812
00:53:54.334 --> 00:53:55.835
Ah. Thank you.

813
00:53:57.045 --> 00:53:59.464
[air-raid siren blaring]

814
00:54:01.549 --> 00:54:04.386
[chiming on radio]

815
00:54:08.640 --> 00:54:10.724
[man on radio] <i>This is an
emergency news broadcast.</i>

816
00:54:10.725 --> 00:54:12.226
<i>Do not turn off your radios.</i>

817
00:54:12.227 --> 00:54:14.895
<i>A giant creature has
come ashore at Tokyo Bay</i>

818
00:54:14.896 --> 00:54:16.772
<i>and is now heading toward Ginza.</i>

819
00:54:16.773 --> 00:54:18.607
<i>To those in or
around the region.</i>

820
00:54:18.608 --> 00:54:21.485
<i>follow police instructions
and evacuate right away.</i>

821
00:54:21.486 --> 00:54:23.112
<i>This is not a hoax.</i>

822
00:54:23.113 --> 00:54:24.363
- Ginza?
- [man] <i>I repeat...</i>

823
00:54:24.364 --> 00:54:26.365
[panicked screaming]

824
00:54:26.366 --> 00:54:29.077
[officer] Go! Go! Go!

825
00:54:29.786 --> 00:54:30.912
[fearful whimpering]

826
00:54:31.621 --> 00:54:33.581
[woman] Oh. are you
hurt? Here. come with me!

827
00:54:37.752 --> 00:54:39.920
- [panicked cries]
- [distant roaring]

828
00:54:39.921 --> 00:54:42.007
[terrified shrieking]

829
00:54:43.300 --> 00:54:44.466
[stunned silence]

830
00:54:44.467 --> 00:54:46.386
[panicked screaming]

831
00:54:59.190 --> 00:55:00.442
[whooshing]

832
00:55:01.526 --> 00:55:02.819
[both screaming]

833
00:55:03.862 --> 00:55:06.364
- [brakes screeching]
- [passengers gasping]

834
00:55:07.365 --> 00:55:09.074
- [woman 1] It stopped?
- Hey. what's going on?

835
00:55:09.075 --> 00:55:11.661
- [woman 2] Why did we stop?
- [thundering footstep]

836
00:55:13.997 --> 00:55:15.248
[thundering footstep]

837
00:55:17.042 --> 00:55:18.835
[ominous music playing]

838
00:55:28.845 --> 00:55:30.763
Is that... [breathing shakily]

839
00:55:30.764 --> 00:55:31.765
Godzilla?

840
00:55:33.725 --> 00:55:36.686
[roaring loudly]

841
00:55:37.729 --> 00:55:39.146
[panicked screaming]

842
00:55:39.147 --> 00:55:40.857
[ominous music playing]

843
00:55:52.786 --> 00:55:54.411
[snarling]

844
00:55:54.412 --> 00:55:55.829
[terrified yelping]

845
00:55:55.830 --> 00:55:57.749
[panicked screaming]

846
00:56:02.462 --> 00:56:04.129
[breathing rapidly]

847
00:56:04.130 --> 00:56:05.465
[Noriko cries fearfully]

848
00:56:07.050 --> 00:56:08.843
[scared whimpering]

849
00:56:11.429 --> 00:56:12.889
[panicked shrieking]

850
00:56:14.974 --> 00:56:16.976
- [metal crunching]
- [glass shattering]

851
00:56:20.855 --> 00:56:22.565
[screaming]

852
00:56:26.903 --> 00:56:28.905
[yelping. hyperventilating]

853
00:56:36.246 --> 00:56:37.664
[strong wind blowing]

854
00:56:38.373 --> 00:56:39.874
[whimpering fearfully]

855
00:56:42.585 --> 00:56:43.585
[determined grunt]

856
00:56:49.843 --> 00:56:52.302
What we're witnessing is
a scene beyond belief.

857
00:56:52.303 --> 00:56:55.347
We can only watch as the massive
creature destroys our city!

858
00:56:55.348 --> 00:56:58.143
Each step it takes. Ginza
is crushed in its path.

859
00:56:59.310 --> 00:57:02.354
And now it's begun tearing
apart the Nippon Theater!

860
00:57:02.355 --> 00:57:04.940
The theater. once a
beloved icon of the people.

861
00:57:04.941 --> 00:57:06.650
razed in mere moments.

862
00:57:06.651 --> 00:57:09.154
All of this. right
before our very eyes!

863
00:57:09.863 --> 00:57:10.697
{\an8}[scared yelping]

864
00:57:10.698 --> 00:57:12.030
{\an8}It's truly unbelievable.

865
00:57:12.031 --> 00:57:15.325
{\an8}The district that survived
catastrophic air raids during the war

866
00:57:15.326 --> 00:57:17.578
{\an8}has been reduced to
little more than rubble.

867
00:57:17.579 --> 00:57:21.123
{\an8}Ah! And now the monster! It's
approaching our position!

868
00:57:21.124 --> 00:57:22.499
As it moves closer.

869
00:57:22.500 --> 00:57:26.795
we can only stand back and watch as
its enormous head towers above us!

870
00:57:26.796 --> 00:57:29.674
This could be the end! It
isn't safe for us to be here!

871
00:57:31.301 --> 00:57:33.093
[unsteady gasping]

872
00:57:33.094 --> 00:57:34.512
[panicked chatter]

873
00:57:36.055 --> 00:57:37.807
[fearful yelping]

874
00:57:39.058 --> 00:57:42.061
[terrified screaming]

875
00:57:42.812 --> 00:57:44.813
[man 1] Run! Move! It's coming!

876
00:57:44.814 --> 00:57:46.399
[panicked screaming]

877
00:57:53.740 --> 00:57:55.533
- [man 2] Move it!
- [Noriko yelps]

878
00:57:59.204 --> 00:58:00.288
[Noriko gasps]

879
00:58:00.788 --> 00:58:02.957
- [thundering footsteps]
- [man 3] Oh God!

880
00:58:03.750 --> 00:58:04.751
[Shikishima] Get up!

881
00:58:05.251 --> 00:58:08.129
- [Noriko] Koichi!
- We have to get out of here! Come on!

882
00:58:10.131 --> 00:58:11.466
[dramatic music playing]

883
00:58:15.094 --> 00:58:16.679
[man 4] Come on! Move!

884
00:58:18.681 --> 00:58:21.559
- [terrified screaming]
- [bodies crunching underfoot]

885
00:58:23.436 --> 00:58:25.146
[screaming]

886
00:58:27.148 --> 00:58:28.273
[explosion]

887
00:58:28.274 --> 00:58:29.274
[Noriko gasps]

888
00:58:31.986 --> 00:58:33.196
[Godzilla screeches]

889
00:58:33.947 --> 00:58:35.323
[dramatic music playing]

890
00:58:40.370 --> 00:58:41.538
[projectiles whizzing]

891
00:58:45.750 --> 00:58:47.292
[heavy gunfire]

892
00:58:47.293 --> 00:58:50.837
[booming thuds]

893
00:58:50.838 --> 00:58:52.506
[hopeful muttering]

894
00:58:52.507 --> 00:58:53.633
[man 5] Is it dead?

895
00:58:55.426 --> 00:58:56.636
[man 6] Did they get it?

896
00:58:58.888 --> 00:59:02.100
[people screaming]

897
00:59:05.019 --> 00:59:06.728
[terrified whimpering]

898
00:59:06.729 --> 00:59:08.940
[foreboding music building]

899
00:59:14.946 --> 00:59:16.466
- [fins clunking]
- [radiation buzzing]

900
00:59:33.965 --> 00:59:36.425
[heat ray rumbling]

901
00:59:36.426 --> 00:59:37.510
Not again.

902
00:59:39.012 --> 00:59:40.263
It's just like the Takao.

903
00:59:46.853 --> 00:59:48.980
- [glass shattering]
- [rumbling]

904
00:59:57.238 --> 00:59:58.864
[sound fades]

905
00:59:58.865 --> 01:00:00.700
- [glass shattering]
- [rumbling]

906
01:00:14.839 --> 01:00:16.507
[rubble clattering]

907
01:00:18.551 --> 01:00:20.094
[gasps. breathing heavily]

908
01:00:21.512 --> 01:00:22.512
[grunts softly]

909
01:00:34.359 --> 01:00:35.360
Noriko.

910
01:00:37.945 --> 01:00:39.030
Noriko!

911
01:00:39.989 --> 01:00:40.989
Uh...

912
01:00:41.532 --> 01:00:43.201
[hesitantly] N... Noriko?

913
01:00:48.998 --> 01:00:51.125
[distraught whimpering]

914
01:00:54.337 --> 01:00:55.338
[shuddering breath]

915
01:00:56.881 --> 01:00:58.257
[distraught whimpering]

916
01:01:06.724 --> 01:01:08.183
[sobbing]

917
01:01:08.184 --> 01:01:09.852
[solemn music playing]

918
01:01:16.109 --> 01:01:17.110
[breathing shakily]

919
01:01:37.463 --> 01:01:39.090
[shuddering breaths]

920
01:01:42.969 --> 01:01:44.971
[Godzilla roaring]

921
01:01:54.772 --> 01:01:56.315
[rubble crunching underfoot]

922
01:02:04.240 --> 01:02:07.118
[yelling angrily]

923
01:02:07.618 --> 01:02:09.996
[anguished screaming]

924
01:02:19.714 --> 01:02:21.423
[man] <i>The damage caused
by the giant creature</i>

925
01:02:21.424 --> 01:02:22.841
<i>that came ashore yesterday</i>

926
01:02:22.842 --> 01:02:25.469
<i>includes a total of some
30.000 killed or injured</i>

927
01:02:25.470 --> 01:02:28.597
{\an8}<i>and over 20.000 homes
and buildings destroyed.</i>

928
01:02:28.598 --> 01:02:31.683
{\an8}<i>Rescue and recovery operations
are already underway.</i>

929
01:02:31.684 --> 01:02:34.186
{\an8}<i>but investigating the wreckage
from the creature's path</i>

930
01:02:34.187 --> 01:02:37.898
<i>carries the risk of radiation.
which has severely impeded progress.</i>

931
01:02:37.899 --> 01:02:40.150
<i>Throughout Ginza. pieces of
the massive beast's flesh</i>

932
01:02:40.151 --> 01:02:43.362
<i>have been discovered after having
apparently peeled off during the attack.</i>

933
01:02:43.946 --> 01:02:46.198
<i>Police have cordoned off
central Ginza all day</i>

934
01:02:46.199 --> 01:02:49.243
<i>to collect samples of any
materials of unknown composition.</i>

935
01:02:52.580 --> 01:02:53.873
[solemn music playing]

936
01:02:59.003 --> 01:03:01.255
[echoing ding]

937
01:03:04.801 --> 01:03:06.260
I still can't believe it.

938
01:03:11.766 --> 01:03:14.018
- What about Akiko?
- [Mizushima] Hm?

939
01:03:15.394 --> 01:03:18.231
We all pull together to
take care of each other.

940
01:03:18.898 --> 01:03:20.066
Hey. Akiko.

941
01:03:22.902 --> 01:03:28.031
Remember. you're going to stay at
my house when Dad's away. okay?

942
01:03:28.032 --> 01:03:30.618
When do I get to see Mom?

943
01:03:36.123 --> 01:03:37.708
Mm. Not right now.

944
01:03:38.876 --> 01:03:41.838
She had to go away for
a little while for work.

945
01:03:42.463 --> 01:03:44.465
So you'll be with
your auntie for a bit.

946
01:03:45.925 --> 01:03:47.552
[Akiko crying]

947
01:03:56.477 --> 01:03:59.062
[Sumiko] Oh. Akiko.
Come here. sweetheart.

948
01:03:59.063 --> 01:04:00.189
It's okay.

949
01:04:01.899 --> 01:04:03.025
It'll be all right.

950
01:04:03.651 --> 01:04:04.735
Come here.

951
01:04:05.403 --> 01:04:06.444
It's okay.

952
01:04:06.445 --> 01:04:08.030
[Akiko continues crying]

953
01:04:31.929 --> 01:04:34.849
It's what I get. isn't
it? For what I did to you.

954
01:04:41.689 --> 01:04:42.689
Of course.

955
01:04:44.650 --> 01:04:46.736
Why did I think I
could dream again?

956
01:04:51.365 --> 01:04:52.365
[chuckles wryly]

957
01:05:01.626 --> 01:05:02.626
Shiki-san.

958
01:05:04.420 --> 01:05:05.504
Listen to me.

959
01:05:06.380 --> 01:05:10.051
I'm part of a secret effort to
design a strategy to defeat Godzilla

960
01:05:11.677 --> 01:05:13.304
led by a civilian force.

961
01:05:14.472 --> 01:05:16.807
While I still don't
know how viable it is...

962
01:05:20.186 --> 01:05:21.562
I'd like you to be there.

963
01:05:28.277 --> 01:05:31.738
SPECIAL DISASTER
COUNTERMEASURE HEARING

964
01:05:31.739 --> 01:05:33.658
[indistinct background chatter]

965
01:05:37.411 --> 01:05:39.829
Look at all these guys.
Is everybody here...

966
01:05:39.830 --> 01:05:42.332
Yes. They're all
ex-navy personnel.

967
01:05:42.333 --> 01:05:43.417
Is that so?

968
01:05:43.918 --> 01:05:44.918
No kidding.

969
01:06:03.646 --> 01:06:05.814
{\an8}My name is Hotta.

970
01:06:05.815 --> 01:06:08.150
{\an8}I was the captain
of the Yukikaze.

971
01:06:08.693 --> 01:06:10.568
Thank you all for coming today.

972
01:06:10.569 --> 01:06:14.531
As you're all aware. Tokyo is
facing an unprecedented threat.

973
01:06:14.532 --> 01:06:16.616
A powerful creature so enormous

974
01:06:16.617 --> 01:06:19.160
that it can level
an entire city.

975
01:06:19.161 --> 01:06:21.664
But we lack defensive
forces of our own.

976
01:06:22.289 --> 01:06:25.083
{\an8}Any GHQ intervention
runs the risk

977
01:06:25.084 --> 01:06:27.670
{\an8}of further escalating
US-Soviet tensions.

978
01:06:28.254 --> 01:06:29.713
{\an8}No one is coming to help us.

979
01:06:29.714 --> 01:06:30.673
[muttering]

980
01:06:30.674 --> 01:06:31.798
[Hotta] In short.

981
01:06:31.799 --> 01:06:34.175
the only option is to
confront this monster.

982
01:06:34.176 --> 01:06:36.511
uniting our strengths
as private citizens.

983
01:06:36.512 --> 01:06:37.762
[disbelieving chatter]

984
01:06:37.763 --> 01:06:40.516
[Hotta] That is why we've
gathered you all here today.

985
01:06:41.017 --> 01:06:44.728
{\an8}Fortunately. after
rounds of negotiations.

986
01:06:44.729 --> 01:06:47.898
{\an8}we secured four destroyers
slated for handover to the UN.

987
01:06:48.399 --> 01:06:50.901
- Are you kidding?
- What are you saying?

988
01:06:51.819 --> 01:06:53.945
That you want us to
get back on navy ships?

989
01:06:53.946 --> 01:06:56.698
Just look at Ginza and
what happened there.

990
01:06:56.699 --> 01:06:58.742
There's nothing we
can do to beat that.

991
01:06:58.743 --> 01:07:02.871
Aren't those boats all disarmed?
What are you expecting us to do?

992
01:07:02.872 --> 01:07:04.998
- That's right! You're dreaming!
- This is insane!

993
01:07:04.999 --> 01:07:08.502
Could you please calm down? That's
exactly what I'm here to explain.

994
01:07:09.086 --> 01:07:10.296
Noda-san?

995
01:07:11.380 --> 01:07:13.507
- I would like to...
- [microphone feedback]

996
01:07:15.301 --> 01:07:16.385
Uh. sorry.

997
01:07:17.595 --> 01:07:19.554
I'd like to start
with an introduction.

998
01:07:19.555 --> 01:07:22.557
My name is Kenji Noda. and I
was a navy technical officer.

999
01:07:22.558 --> 01:07:24.769
What we know about
this monster is.

1000
01:07:25.394 --> 01:07:28.646
uh. the local people of Odo
Island call it Godzilla.

1001
01:07:28.647 --> 01:07:30.231
which is how I'll refer to it.

1002
01:07:30.232 --> 01:07:33.902
This creature is virtually immune to
all types of conventional weaponry.

1003
01:07:33.903 --> 01:07:35.320
I witnessed it firsthand.

1004
01:07:35.321 --> 01:07:37.989
As soon as the Takao hit
it with its heavy cannons.

1005
01:07:37.990 --> 01:07:41.327
Godzilla began regenerating
itself back to health.

1006
01:07:41.911 --> 01:07:43.953
What can we do against
a thing like that?

1007
01:07:43.954 --> 01:07:45.371
Quiet. please.

1008
01:07:45.372 --> 01:07:48.000
Our plan will instead
use the unconventional.

1009
01:07:50.336 --> 01:07:52.837
Please. allow us to
show you what I mean.

1010
01:07:52.838 --> 01:07:56.217
The water in this tank has
the same salinity as seawater.

1011
01:07:56.717 --> 01:07:58.927
There's a wooden Godzilla
model on the surface.

1012
01:07:58.928 --> 01:08:01.888
which you can see we've weighed down
just enough to float at the top.

1013
01:08:01.889 --> 01:08:03.598
If we were to pipe in Freon gas.

1014
01:08:03.599 --> 01:08:06.768
what would happen once the
model is enveloped in bubbles?

1015
01:08:06.769 --> 01:08:08.686
Oh. now that's an easy one.

1016
01:08:08.687 --> 01:08:10.897
It'll stay afloat.
even with the bubbles.

1017
01:08:10.898 --> 01:08:13.483
- What else could it do?
- [man 2] Yeah. it'll float!

1018
01:08:13.484 --> 01:08:15.277
Yes. that's what
you would think.

1019
01:08:18.572 --> 01:08:19.782
[gas hissing]

1020
01:08:21.700 --> 01:08:23.451
- [man 3] Oh God.
- [man 4] It sank!

1021
01:08:23.452 --> 01:08:25.370
- [man 5] It did?
- [man 6] Yeah.

1022
01:08:25.371 --> 01:08:27.664
The Freon bubbles
surround the wooden model.

1023
01:08:27.665 --> 01:08:29.958
which prevents any
contact with seawater.

1024
01:08:29.959 --> 01:08:32.669
The idea is to trap the
real Godzilla just like this

1025
01:08:32.670 --> 01:08:35.505
and forcefully sink the creature
to the bottom of the ocean.

1026
01:08:35.506 --> 01:08:39.968
Hey. Looks like the Doc carries a
lot of influence around here. huh?

1027
01:08:39.969 --> 01:08:40.886
Uh-huh.

1028
01:08:40.887 --> 01:08:42.888
[men chattering indistinctly]

1029
01:08:54.150 --> 01:08:55.400
Now. as you're all aware.

1030
01:08:55.401 --> 01:08:58.069
the Sagami Trench is
over 1.500 meters deep.

1031
01:08:58.070 --> 01:09:01.239
making it the single deepest
point in nearby waters.

1032
01:09:01.240 --> 01:09:02.323
And so my plan

1033
01:09:02.324 --> 01:09:05.243
is to attach our Freon gas
cylinders directly to Godzilla

1034
01:09:05.244 --> 01:09:06.703
and fire them all at once.

1035
01:09:06.704 --> 01:09:08.788
surrounding it in a bubble
membrane like you saw.

1036
01:09:08.789 --> 01:09:12.041
The idea is that it will sink to
the bottom of the trench so rapidly.

1037
01:09:12.042 --> 01:09:13.543
the pressure will
crush it to death.

1038
01:09:13.544 --> 01:09:15.254
[men chattering indistinctly]

1039
01:09:16.881 --> 01:09:19.133
We kill it with the
power of the ocean.

1040
01:09:20.176 --> 01:09:23.720
I call it... Special
Operation Wada Tsumi.

1041
01:09:23.721 --> 01:09:24.888
[man 7] "Wada Tsumi"?

1042
01:09:24.889 --> 01:09:28.766
Couldn't it withstand the pressure if
it's already used to living in the sea?

1043
01:09:28.767 --> 01:09:29.893
[man 8] Yeah!

1044
01:09:29.894 --> 01:09:33.229
The calculations show
that after 25 seconds.

1045
01:09:33.230 --> 01:09:36.649
every square meter should
apply 1.500 tons of pressure.

1046
01:09:36.650 --> 01:09:39.068
Even a creature that's used
to living in deep water

1047
01:09:39.069 --> 01:09:42.155
would be extremely unlikely to
survive that kind of pressure.

1048
01:09:42.156 --> 01:09:43.657
I have a question.

1049
01:09:44.158 --> 01:09:46.452
Can you guarantee this
will kill Godzilla?

1050
01:09:48.829 --> 01:09:51.665
Godzilla is a creature about
which we know very little.

1051
01:09:52.333 --> 01:09:54.459
So theory has to
drive our strategy.

1052
01:09:54.460 --> 01:09:55.585
[dismissive chatter]

1053
01:09:55.586 --> 01:09:58.379
- [man 9] You call that a plan?
- [man 10] What if it doesn't work?

1054
01:09:58.380 --> 01:10:01.216
Guns can't hurt it. as I've
said. so we think this is our...

1055
01:10:01.217 --> 01:10:03.344
Just tell us if this
will kill it or not.

1056
01:10:06.388 --> 01:10:07.890
I can't guarantee that.

1057
01:10:08.390 --> 01:10:09.892
[disappointed murmuring]

1058
01:10:10.851 --> 01:10:11.851
Shikishima!

1059
01:10:12.269 --> 01:10:13.686
This is our best shot!

1060
01:10:13.687 --> 01:10:15.272
[pensive music playing]

1061
01:10:18.442 --> 01:10:19.568
Shiki-san.

1062
01:10:21.612 --> 01:10:23.112
Just hear me out. all right?

1063
01:10:23.113 --> 01:10:24.448
[pensive music continues]

1064
01:10:40.381 --> 01:10:42.925
Now. then. Here is step one.

1065
01:10:48.138 --> 01:10:51.976
Two destroyers will corral Godzilla
and wrap it in a cable like this.

1066
01:10:53.018 --> 01:10:55.895
Running along the cable
will be various points

1067
01:10:55.896 --> 01:10:58.607
that have Freon gas
cylinders attached to them.

1068
01:11:01.026 --> 01:11:04.488
Once it's wrapped tightly.
the gas can then be released.

1069
01:11:05.572 --> 01:11:09.742
This will force Godzilla to
rapidly plunge down 1.500 meters.

1070
01:11:09.743 --> 01:11:11.494
If it doesn't
work. what happens?

1071
01:11:11.495 --> 01:11:13.162
There's a contingency for that.

1072
01:11:13.163 --> 01:11:14.372
[men muttering]

1073
01:11:14.373 --> 01:11:17.418
Gentlemen. would you
look into the courtyard?

1074
01:11:24.842 --> 01:11:26.510
[suspenseful music playing]

1075
01:11:34.935 --> 01:11:37.104
- [suspenseful music intensifies]
- Inflate!

1076
01:11:37.855 --> 01:11:39.188
[men] Whoa!

1077
01:11:39.189 --> 01:11:41.650
- [impressed muttering]
- [man 10] That was crazy!

1078
01:11:42.443 --> 01:11:46.696
Hello. I'm Itagaki from Toyo Balloon.
Let me explain what you just saw.

1079
01:11:46.697 --> 01:11:50.658
For this design. we chose to look
at the life rafts used in the war.

1080
01:11:50.659 --> 01:11:52.827
It's an inflatable
flotation device.

1081
01:11:52.828 --> 01:11:56.289
CO2 is shot at high velocity
into air sacs for buoyancy.

1082
01:11:56.290 --> 01:11:58.375
Think of it like
a life preserver.

1083
01:11:59.835 --> 01:12:01.753
Once Godzilla hits the bottom.

1084
01:12:01.754 --> 01:12:05.465
the device is inflated. forcing
it right back up to the surface.

1085
01:12:05.466 --> 01:12:08.051
Even if it does initially
withstand the pressure.

1086
01:12:08.052 --> 01:12:11.680
in these conditions. it's highly
unlikely to survive decompression.

1087
01:12:12.264 --> 01:12:15.934
Even so. I can't tell you that this
will work with total certainty.

1088
01:12:16.727 --> 01:12:19.020
But I think this is gonna
be our only real chance.

1089
01:12:19.021 --> 01:12:20.814
[hesitant murmuring]

1090
01:12:24.360 --> 01:12:26.612
I doubt that any of
us want to be here.

1091
01:12:27.237 --> 01:12:30.365
Putting your lives on the line
after already surviving a war.

1092
01:12:30.366 --> 01:12:32.075
I know how unfair it sounds.

1093
01:12:32.076 --> 01:12:34.661
And yet. we need your help.

1094
01:12:35.287 --> 01:12:38.290
We're in this alone. No
aid from any government.

1095
01:12:39.083 --> 01:12:42.378
Which means the future of this
nation is in your hands again.

1096
01:12:43.128 --> 01:12:44.546
[music fades]

1097
01:12:45.381 --> 01:12:46.465
I can't. sir.

1098
01:12:48.425 --> 01:12:50.426
It's too much. I have a family.

1099
01:12:50.427 --> 01:12:53.430
Everyone here does. Why do we
have to risk our lives again?

1100
01:12:54.139 --> 01:12:57.810
Why does it have to be us? We're always
the ones drawing the short straw.

1101
01:12:59.353 --> 01:13:01.771
We can't go back to the things
we were doing in the war.

1102
01:13:01.772 --> 01:13:03.690
[men chattering indistinctly]

1103
01:13:04.817 --> 01:13:06.568
[all calling out hesitations]

1104
01:13:07.986 --> 01:13:09.237
[Hotta] Quiet. please.

1105
01:13:09.238 --> 01:13:11.949
Please. Listen carefully.

1106
01:13:13.033 --> 01:13:14.535
We aren't conscripting you.

1107
01:13:15.119 --> 01:13:18.539
If you don't want to volunteer for
this. go back to your families.

1108
01:13:19.164 --> 01:13:22.292
None of us have the
right to stop any of you.

1109
01:13:26.588 --> 01:13:28.047
- [man 11] Hey.
- [man 12] What?

1110
01:13:28.048 --> 01:13:29.465
[man 13] He's gonna leave?

1111
01:13:29.466 --> 01:13:30.591
Hold on.

1112
01:13:30.592 --> 01:13:31.677
[man 14] Excuse me.

1113
01:13:33.303 --> 01:13:34.555
[indistinct muttering]

1114
01:13:36.140 --> 01:13:37.391
[man 15] I'm sorry. sir.

1115
01:13:44.273 --> 01:13:46.441
[murmuring dies down]

1116
01:13:46.442 --> 01:13:47.901
[man 16] I have a question.

1117
01:13:49.278 --> 01:13:51.321
Does this plan of yours
mean certain death?

1118
01:13:52.239 --> 01:13:53.740
Of course it doesn't.

1119
01:13:56.118 --> 01:13:59.203
Okay. Well. those odds
are better than the war.

1120
01:13:59.204 --> 01:14:00.956
[laughter]

1121
01:14:02.166 --> 01:14:04.126
[man 16] Someone
has to do it. right?

1122
01:14:05.002 --> 01:14:06.752
Who else is gonna get this done?

1123
01:14:06.753 --> 01:14:09.464
We need these ships. and
that means we need sailors.

1124
01:14:09.465 --> 01:14:11.716
- [man 17] Yeah.
- [man 18] That's true.

1125
01:14:11.717 --> 01:14:14.844
What do you say?
Are we in. boys?

1126
01:14:14.845 --> 01:14:17.597
[men shouting] Yes! Yes! Yeah!

1127
01:14:17.598 --> 01:14:18.764
[man 19] Sure am!

1128
01:14:18.765 --> 01:14:20.433
[man 20] Let's do it! Come on!

1129
01:14:20.434 --> 01:14:21.894
- Let's go!
- Let's do it!

1130
01:14:23.020 --> 01:14:24.980
- [man 21] We can do it!
- My friends.

1131
01:14:27.483 --> 01:14:28.483
Thank you.

1132
01:14:28.817 --> 01:14:30.318
- Yes!
- Yes!

1133
01:14:30.319 --> 01:14:31.570
Hear. hear!

1134
01:14:33.947 --> 01:14:35.407
[applause continues]

1135
01:14:38.202 --> 01:14:39.952
That was a surprise.

1136
01:14:39.953 --> 01:14:43.289
finding out our good ol' Doc was
the one behind this crazy plan.

1137
01:14:43.290 --> 01:14:46.792
[chuckling] Well. I've had a
direct encounter with Godzilla.

1138
01:14:46.793 --> 01:14:49.587
Because of that. they
suggested that I take the lead.

1139
01:14:49.588 --> 01:14:53.049
Ah. that makes sense. That's why
they wanted us there too. isn't it?

1140
01:14:53.050 --> 01:14:56.136
So. you think
Godzilla will return?

1141
01:14:57.304 --> 01:14:59.138
After that last attack.

1142
01:14:59.139 --> 01:15:02.058
we can assume that
Godzilla has added Tokyo

1143
01:15:02.059 --> 01:15:03.809
to its new "territory" of sorts.

1144
01:15:03.810 --> 01:15:06.646
Which would mean.
in the worst case.

1145
01:15:06.647 --> 01:15:08.440
it could return within ten days.

1146
01:15:08.941 --> 01:15:10.107
You think that soon?

1147
01:15:10.108 --> 01:15:13.110
I heard you set up
radiation-detecting buoys all over.

1148
01:15:13.111 --> 01:15:16.197
We can't just rely on our sight
to figure out where it is.

1149
01:15:16.198 --> 01:15:17.573
Yeah. still. though.

1150
01:15:17.574 --> 01:15:20.786
you really think it's gonna walk
into your trap just like that?

1151
01:15:21.286 --> 01:15:23.371
- Well. that's the thing.
- What. you don't have a plan?

1152
01:15:23.372 --> 01:15:26.917
Well. yes. of course I do. Who
do you think you're dealing with?

1153
01:15:29.670 --> 01:15:32.588
We have underwater speakers
used for acoustic minesweeping.

1154
01:15:32.589 --> 01:15:34.173
We use the speakers to play

1155
01:15:34.174 --> 01:15:37.385
the recordings made of Godzilla's
voice during its last attack.

1156
01:15:37.386 --> 01:15:38.971
- Godzilla's voice?
- Yeah.

1157
01:15:39.471 --> 01:15:40.638
So it'll show up

1158
01:15:40.639 --> 01:15:43.934
thinking it has another territorial
competitor to deal with.

1159
01:15:44.726 --> 01:15:46.061
- Hopefully.
- Hopefully?!

1160
01:15:46.603 --> 01:15:48.396
You can't just rely on hope.

1161
01:15:48.397 --> 01:15:51.482
And what was that...
"flotation device" thing?

1162
01:15:51.483 --> 01:15:54.569
I don't see how that'll work on
something as big as Godzilla.

1163
01:15:54.570 --> 01:15:56.821
I'd like to see you
think of something else.

1164
01:15:56.822 --> 01:16:00.241
I know! What about pulling
it up using the destroyers?

1165
01:16:00.242 --> 01:16:01.826
You insane? They
couldn't do that.

1166
01:16:01.827 --> 01:16:05.746
Godzilla weighs around 20.000 tons.
That's far too heavy for two destroyers.

1167
01:16:05.747 --> 01:16:07.332
Uh... Oh.

1168
01:16:09.001 --> 01:16:12.337
In short. Doc. I think your
plan has a lot of holes in it.

1169
01:16:12.963 --> 01:16:16.800
Well. if you're just gonna complain.
why don't you come up with a better one?

1170
01:16:19.052 --> 01:16:20.178
[Shikishima] Noda-san.

1171
01:16:22.180 --> 01:16:25.601
If I asked you for a fighter.
could you get me one?

1172
01:16:26.476 --> 01:16:27.602
A fighter?

1173
01:16:27.603 --> 01:16:29.645
If it does decide
to come ashore.

1174
01:16:29.646 --> 01:16:32.441
I think I could use my guns
to draw it out to the bay.

1175
01:16:33.025 --> 01:16:35.986
But I thought all the Japanese fighters
were decommissioned after the war.

1176
01:16:36.653 --> 01:16:39.990
Besides. even if I could. it
shoots out that heat ray as well.

1177
01:16:40.490 --> 01:16:43.242
Flying so close to it like that.
you'd be risking your life.

1178
01:16:43.243 --> 01:16:45.244
I don't care what the risks are!

1179
01:16:45.245 --> 01:16:49.081
Besides. a good fighter is going to
outrun and outmaneuver any of our boats.

1180
01:16:49.082 --> 01:16:50.791
Are you asking us to
help you with this

1181
01:16:50.792 --> 01:16:53.128
because you really think
it's going to work.

1182
01:16:53.837 --> 01:16:55.464
or are you just trying to die?

1183
01:16:57.090 --> 01:16:58.090
I think you're drunk.

1184
01:16:58.592 --> 01:17:00.761
I think you just
wanna avenge Noriko.

1185
01:17:02.137 --> 01:17:03.262
What's so wrong with that?

1186
01:17:03.263 --> 01:17:05.265
You waited too long.

1187
01:17:07.351 --> 01:17:10.646
Why the hell didn't you marry
that girl when you had the chance?

1188
01:17:11.271 --> 01:17:13.064
You knew how she
felt. didn't you?

1189
01:17:13.065 --> 01:17:15.525
Don't you think I
also wanted that?

1190
01:17:16.568 --> 01:17:18.862
Then why didn't you
say anything to her?

1191
01:17:20.989 --> 01:17:22.157
Because I couldn't.

1192
01:17:28.997 --> 01:17:30.582
My war isn't over yet.

1193
01:17:56.358 --> 01:17:57.983
Is it true? You found a plane?

1194
01:17:57.984 --> 01:18:00.779
Yeah. However. it
is a bit unique.

1195
01:18:09.955 --> 01:18:11.415
[resolute music playing]

1196
01:18:20.173 --> 01:18:22.425
[man] It was developed
at the end of the war.

1197
01:18:22.426 --> 01:18:25.262
A short-range interceptor
known as the Shinden.

1198
01:18:26.471 --> 01:18:28.973
Built to utilize fast
hit-and-run tactics.

1199
01:18:28.974 --> 01:18:31.559
It can hit speeds
of over 400 knots.

1200
01:18:31.560 --> 01:18:34.438
It's a canard design
with four 30 mm guns.

1201
01:18:35.021 --> 01:18:37.106
It can outmaneuver
almost anything.

1202
01:18:37.107 --> 01:18:39.776
A true marvel of
aeronautical innovation.

1203
01:18:40.902 --> 01:18:44.906
The fighters like this one here were
never deployed before the surrender.

1204
01:18:45.407 --> 01:18:48.701
Towards the end of the war. they
were all kept here for storage.

1205
01:18:48.702 --> 01:18:51.538
Until. eventually. they were
forgotten about entirely.

1206
01:18:52.539 --> 01:18:56.418
Since then. they've just sat here to
rust. This one's in pretty bad shape.

1207
01:18:57.753 --> 01:19:00.171
It's not airworthy. Not yet.

1208
01:19:00.172 --> 01:19:03.299
Well. you see. that's the
issue. We need a top mechanic.

1209
01:19:03.300 --> 01:19:07.345
Or an engineer that really knows
their way around a fighter.

1210
01:19:09.931 --> 01:19:13.226
Actually. I know
just the person.

1211
01:19:15.979 --> 01:19:18.898
Let's see. An Ex-Odo Island
detachment mechanic...

1212
01:19:18.899 --> 01:19:21.358
- Sosaku Tachibana. you said?
- Right.

1213
01:19:21.359 --> 01:19:24.403
Tachibana. Tachibana.
Tachibana. Tachibana. let's see.

1214
01:19:24.404 --> 01:19:27.990
Ah. It looks like we don't
have a current address.

1215
01:19:27.991 --> 01:19:29.408
[Shikishima] I understand.

1216
01:19:29.409 --> 01:19:32.369
We're getting hit hard with all
sorts of requests like this.

1217
01:19:32.370 --> 01:19:34.705
It could take quite a bit of
time for us to find anything.

1218
01:19:34.706 --> 01:19:37.666
You don't understand. I need to
speak with him as soon as I can.

1219
01:19:37.667 --> 01:19:40.586
That's too bad. Sorry. I
don't know what else I can do.

1220
01:19:40.587 --> 01:19:41.629
- Sir. please!
- What?

1221
01:19:41.630 --> 01:19:45.132
[Shikishima] I'm begging you! The
country's future depends on it!

1222
01:19:45.133 --> 01:19:48.511
Oh. it does. I'm sure. But
I can't do the impossible.

1223
01:19:48.512 --> 01:19:49.512
So sorry.

1224
01:19:49.513 --> 01:19:50.847
Ah. Hold on.

1225
01:19:51.473 --> 01:19:52.307
Uh. Tachibana.

1226
01:19:52.308 --> 01:19:54.934
Do you know where he was posted
before he got to Odo Island?

1227
01:19:54.935 --> 01:19:56.436
Can you at least tell me that?

1228
01:19:56.937 --> 01:19:58.396
[resolute music continues]

1229
01:20:03.902 --> 01:20:06.237
I've already asked
everywhere I can.

1230
01:20:06.238 --> 01:20:08.113
But this Tachibana fellow.

1231
01:20:08.114 --> 01:20:10.534
he's proving to be quite
hard to track down.

1232
01:20:11.409 --> 01:20:14.578
We can find someone else to help
us get the plane up in the air.

1233
01:20:14.579 --> 01:20:16.288
Think. Do you have
any other leads?

1234
01:20:16.289 --> 01:20:18.124
Please just wait
a little longer.

1235
01:20:19.793 --> 01:20:22.461
I don't know why you're being
so insistent. Shiki-san.

1236
01:20:22.462 --> 01:20:23.963
Godzilla could come back soon.

1237
01:20:23.964 --> 01:20:26.508
- We can't be wasting...
- It's got to be Tachibana. all right?!

1238
01:20:27.259 --> 01:20:29.719
I'm sure he'll get the
message soon. He has to.

1239
01:20:30.679 --> 01:20:32.013
Wait for him. please.

1240
01:20:35.100 --> 01:20:36.101
[music fades]

1241
01:20:36.726 --> 01:20:37.811
[footsteps following]

1242
01:20:43.316 --> 01:20:44.526
[both grunting]

1243
01:20:52.659 --> 01:20:54.160
[gasping]

1244
01:20:55.203 --> 01:20:57.706
[Shikishima breathing nervously]

1245
01:20:58.623 --> 01:21:00.041
T... Tachibana?

1246
01:21:01.877 --> 01:21:04.254
Tachibana-san! It really is you!

1247
01:21:08.967 --> 01:21:10.927
What the hell are all
these letters about?

1248
01:21:13.763 --> 01:21:15.223
[Shikishima groans] Wait.

1249
01:21:16.433 --> 01:21:18.142
[breathing shakily. grunts]

1250
01:21:18.143 --> 01:21:20.312
The Odo Island
massacre was my fault?

1251
01:21:20.896 --> 01:21:22.689
I'm the one who
let those men die?

1252
01:21:24.733 --> 01:21:26.318
What are you talking about?

1253
01:21:27.152 --> 01:21:28.153
I'm sorry.

1254
01:21:28.987 --> 01:21:30.322
I needed you to find me.

1255
01:21:30.822 --> 01:21:34.742
And sending those was the one thing
I knew would get under your skin.

1256
01:21:34.743 --> 01:21:36.786
- [Tachibana] How dare you?!
- [grunts]

1257
01:21:38.622 --> 01:21:40.457
The monster that attacked Ginza

1258
01:21:41.291 --> 01:21:42.834
was the same one from Odo.

1259
01:21:44.336 --> 01:21:45.462
It was Godzilla.

1260
01:21:50.842 --> 01:21:53.178
[Shikishima groaning softly]

1261
01:21:53.887 --> 01:21:55.096
We have a fighter.

1262
01:21:55.764 --> 01:21:57.723
We're gonna use it
to try and kill it.

1263
01:21:57.724 --> 01:21:59.643
And I need your help to fix it.

1264
01:22:00.685 --> 01:22:02.270
That's why I had to find you.

1265
01:22:02.896 --> 01:22:05.315
We need a mechanic who
can get it ready to fly.

1266
01:22:06.232 --> 01:22:08.443
That's why I wrote all
those stupid letters.

1267
01:22:09.152 --> 01:22:10.235
[pained grunt]

1268
01:22:10.236 --> 01:22:11.655
Please forgive me!

1269
01:22:12.697 --> 01:22:14.616
[sobbing]

1270
01:22:16.034 --> 01:22:17.201
[grunts]

1271
01:22:17.202 --> 01:22:18.912
Forget it. You're on your own.

1272
01:22:20.705 --> 01:22:22.123
Why would I ever help you?

1273
01:22:22.832 --> 01:22:24.041
[Shikishima] Tachibana!

1274
01:22:24.042 --> 01:22:26.002
Please. wait. Tachibana!

1275
01:22:26.503 --> 01:22:27.379
Please don't go!

1276
01:22:27.380 --> 01:22:30.882
Tachibana! I need you
to do something for me!

1277
01:22:31.383 --> 01:22:35.220
Something... something I
know that only you can do.

1278
01:22:36.888 --> 01:22:38.430
The Takao's guns did nothing.

1279
01:22:38.431 --> 01:22:41.892
but I detonated a mine in its
mouth. and it actually hurt it.

1280
01:22:41.893 --> 01:22:45.230
I think we can kill it if we find
a way to hit it from the inside!

1281
01:22:47.023 --> 01:22:48.023
You mean...

1282
01:22:49.567 --> 01:22:52.695
Put explosives in the rig and
fly directly into its mouth

1283
01:22:52.696 --> 01:22:54.906
so we can finally kill
it once and for all.

1284
01:23:01.830 --> 01:23:03.039
A kamikaze.

1285
01:23:05.375 --> 01:23:07.002
The war isn't over yet.

1286
01:23:10.338 --> 01:23:12.132
Not for me or for you.

1287
01:23:15.051 --> 01:23:16.469
Aah...

1288
01:23:17.095 --> 01:23:19.513
- I thought you said you just fell down.
- Ah!

1289
01:23:19.514 --> 01:23:22.641
You had to hit yourself pretty
hard for it to swell up that much.

1290
01:23:22.642 --> 01:23:26.353
[chuckles] It's embarrassing. I
ended up getting pretty drunk.

1291
01:23:26.354 --> 01:23:28.064
I barely remember anything.

1292
01:23:28.606 --> 01:23:31.567
Well. considering you found
Tachibana after looking so hard.

1293
01:23:31.568 --> 01:23:33.902
I think you deserved
to celebrate a little.

1294
01:23:33.903 --> 01:23:36.489
- [Shikishima chuckles]
- [Tachibana] A canard. huh?

1295
01:23:38.033 --> 01:23:40.535
I didn't think that they
had actually finished one.

1296
01:23:42.912 --> 01:23:45.581
Tachibana-san. You made it.

1297
01:23:45.582 --> 01:23:47.249
Thank you all for coming!

1298
01:23:47.250 --> 01:23:49.461
[Noda] Hello. You
must be Mr. Tachibana.

1299
01:23:52.881 --> 01:23:56.884
Look at that. Must be one of the
Shinden class interceptors. huh?

1300
01:23:56.885 --> 01:24:00.388
Yes. This one wasn't finished.
You think you can make it fly?

1301
01:24:03.558 --> 01:24:05.894
We'll do everything we
can to make that happen.

1302
01:24:06.394 --> 01:24:07.729
We really appreciate it.

1303
01:24:08.938 --> 01:24:09.939
Good luck.

1304
01:24:10.607 --> 01:24:11.607
Good luck.

1305
01:24:14.319 --> 01:24:17.155
- [purposeful music playing]
- [man] Move out! Move it out!

1306
01:24:17.947 --> 01:24:18.947
Come on!

1307
01:24:19.532 --> 01:24:20.532
Get it on!

1308
01:24:21.826 --> 01:24:23.328
All right. let's pick it up!

1309
01:24:23.912 --> 01:24:25.872
- Get those crates on now!
- Yes. sir!

1310
01:24:26.539 --> 01:24:29.084
[man] Hey! Get moving. boys!

1311
01:24:29.793 --> 01:24:30.794
What's wrong?

1312
01:24:31.628 --> 01:24:34.838
You need to lighten up a little.
Doc. It ain't good for morale.

1313
01:24:34.839 --> 01:24:36.965
I know that this was
my idea. and yet.

1314
01:24:36.966 --> 01:24:41.261
I still worry that for everything to work.
we'll need some kind of miracle to happen.

1315
01:24:41.262 --> 01:24:42.763
I know you're worried.

1316
01:24:42.764 --> 01:24:46.183
But to get a miracle. you don't
just stand by and wait for one.

1317
01:24:46.184 --> 01:24:47.310
Yes. you're right.

1318
01:24:48.186 --> 01:24:49.521
Take a look out there.

1319
01:24:50.105 --> 01:24:51.356
These guys know.

1320
01:24:52.649 --> 01:24:53.900
They aren't naive.

1321
01:24:54.609 --> 01:24:57.862
They understand they're putting
their lives at risk to do this.

1322
01:24:58.613 --> 01:24:59.613
And yet.

1323
01:25:00.532 --> 01:25:01.741
their faces.

1324
01:25:02.242 --> 01:25:03.993
they're bright and beaming.

1325
01:25:04.661 --> 01:25:06.787
That's because they
know this time.

1326
01:25:06.788 --> 01:25:09.124
they have a chance to
make a real difference.

1327
01:25:10.208 --> 01:25:12.252
A real difference? Ah.

1328
01:25:14.045 --> 01:25:16.589
In the war. we were used
to suffering every day.

1329
01:25:17.382 --> 01:25:18.383
But now.

1330
01:25:19.300 --> 01:25:20.802
we get to do good again.

1331
01:25:28.017 --> 01:25:29.435
[beacon crackling]

1332
01:25:32.981 --> 01:25:36.191
{\an8}2F CONFERENCE ROOM 3 SPECIAL
DISASTER COUNTERMEASURE HQ

1333
01:25:36.192 --> 01:25:37.192
[man 1] Hurry up!

1334
01:25:37.193 --> 01:25:38.444
[indistinct chattering]

1335
01:25:40.488 --> 01:25:41.489
Make some room.

1336
01:25:43.158 --> 01:25:44.284
This just came in.

1337
01:25:44.909 --> 01:25:46.369
East of Hachijo Island.

1338
01:25:47.078 --> 01:25:49.163
33.1 degrees north.

1339
01:25:49.164 --> 01:25:51.165
140.01 degrees east.

1340
01:25:51.166 --> 01:25:53.458
Geiger readings from
multiple detection buoys

1341
01:25:53.459 --> 01:25:54.669
about an hour ago.

1342
01:25:55.336 --> 01:25:56.378
Followed by

1343
01:25:56.379 --> 01:25:58.548
here and here.

1344
01:26:14.272 --> 01:26:15.940
[Noda] Godzilla is on its way.

1345
01:26:16.858 --> 01:26:18.233
[man 2] It's happening.

1346
01:26:18.234 --> 01:26:20.485
{\an8}If it continues at
this current rate.

1347
01:26:20.486 --> 01:26:23.614
{\an8}Godzilla is expected to
arrive at the Sagami Trench

1348
01:26:23.615 --> 01:26:26.408
{\an8}at approximately
1100 hours tomorrow.

1349
01:26:26.409 --> 01:26:29.995
{\an8}That means we need to leave
port right at 0800 hours.

1350
01:26:29.996 --> 01:26:31.831
{\an8}- [man 3] Mm.
- [men muttering]

1351
01:26:32.582 --> 01:26:33.541
Itagaki.

1352
01:26:33.542 --> 01:26:36.502
Your flotation device. it'll
be ready by then. right?

1353
01:26:37.879 --> 01:26:39.922
We should be there
on the destroyers.

1354
01:26:39.923 --> 01:26:41.966
The final three hours
will be critical.

1355
01:26:42.467 --> 01:26:44.259
As engineers. we
demand perfection.

1356
01:26:44.260 --> 01:26:47.931
I can't ask that. You could get caught
up in our fight against Godzilla.

1357
01:26:48.848 --> 01:26:50.767
The four of us
have seen war too.

1358
01:26:56.856 --> 01:26:59.775
Then. everyone. you
should all go home.

1359
01:26:59.776 --> 01:27:03.863
Spend as much time as you can
with your families tonight.

1360
01:27:05.448 --> 01:27:07.575
Are you saying that we
should prepare them?

1361
01:27:12.038 --> 01:27:13.248
We all know that

1362
01:27:14.457 --> 01:27:18.836
for too long. this country has
treated our lives far too cheaply.

1363
01:27:20.171 --> 01:27:21.923
Tanks with insufficient armor.

1364
01:27:23.049 --> 01:27:24.383
Poor supply chains.

1365
01:27:24.384 --> 01:27:26.510
leading to starvation
and disease.

1366
01:27:26.511 --> 01:27:29.264
causing the most
casualties during the war.

1367
01:27:30.598 --> 01:27:34.059
Fighter planes built
without ejection seats.

1368
01:27:34.060 --> 01:27:35.853
which should be
the bare minimum.

1369
01:27:37.313 --> 01:27:38.313
And finally.

1370
01:27:39.190 --> 01:27:41.192
kamikaze and suicide attacks.

1371
01:27:43.361 --> 01:27:45.321
Those are the reasons
why. this time.

1372
01:27:47.073 --> 01:27:49.409
I want this citizen-led
effort of ours...

1373
01:27:51.577 --> 01:27:54.455
to be one that aims to
sacrifice no lives at all!

1374
01:27:56.416 --> 01:27:58.167
Because this next battle

1375
01:27:59.252 --> 01:28:01.170
isn't about a
fight to the death.

1376
01:28:02.463 --> 01:28:05.008
This battle is a fight
to live for our future.

1377
01:28:08.094 --> 01:28:10.929
All right. yes!
Okay! Let's do this!

1378
01:28:10.930 --> 01:28:13.891
[indistinct chatter overlapping]

1379
01:28:16.686 --> 01:28:19.814
- [resolute music playing]
- Finally. tomorrow's the day.

1380
01:28:20.315 --> 01:28:21.648
Look at me. I'm shivering.

1381
01:28:21.649 --> 01:28:23.067
You're not going. Kid.

1382
01:28:25.028 --> 01:28:26.737
[chuckles] What do you mean?

1383
01:28:26.738 --> 01:28:30.074
We're not gonna have any use for
you while your arm is like that.

1384
01:28:30.700 --> 01:28:32.285
Shikishima still gets to go.

1385
01:28:33.161 --> 01:28:35.329
Hold on. Is this 'cause
I wasn't in the war?

1386
01:28:35.330 --> 01:28:37.164
I can help you. I'm not useless!

1387
01:28:37.165 --> 01:28:38.373
Look. Kid.

1388
01:28:38.374 --> 01:28:40.001
Not being part of a war

1389
01:28:41.085 --> 01:28:43.004
is something to be grateful for.

1390
01:28:49.802 --> 01:28:51.971
I still wanna defend
my country too.

1391
01:28:55.141 --> 01:28:57.435
I don't understand
why I don't get to go!

1392
01:28:59.812 --> 01:29:02.899
I thought we were a team.
that we were in this together!

1393
01:29:04.442 --> 01:29:05.526
Don't do this!

1394
01:29:06.861 --> 01:29:08.529
I wanna be there with you!

1395
01:29:09.238 --> 01:29:11.031
Let me go! Please!

1396
01:29:11.032 --> 01:29:13.658
We're leaving this
country's future with you.

1397
01:29:13.659 --> 01:29:14.952
[Mizushima] Captain!

1398
01:29:15.578 --> 01:29:16.746
Noda-san!

1399
01:29:18.331 --> 01:29:19.748
[man 1] Good. Good.

1400
01:29:19.749 --> 01:29:22.168
- [gentle scraping]
- [man 1] Now bring it up.

1401
01:29:23.044 --> 01:29:24.252
Steady the front end.

1402
01:29:24.253 --> 01:29:25.671
Good. Careful now.

1403
01:29:28.299 --> 01:29:29.300
A little bit lower.

1404
01:29:30.635 --> 01:29:31.635
Easy.

1405
01:29:40.103 --> 01:29:41.270
[music fades]

1406
01:29:46.067 --> 01:29:48.318
Akiko. you ready?

1407
01:29:48.319 --> 01:29:50.363
- Here.
- Okay. Here you go.

1408
01:29:52.615 --> 01:29:53.866
And I'll see you soon.

1409
01:29:59.205 --> 01:30:00.580
- And - Mm?

1410
01:30:00.581 --> 01:30:01.581
Sumiko?

1411
01:30:02.583 --> 01:30:03.876
Thank you for everything.

1412
01:30:17.306 --> 01:30:18.307
Akiko.

1413
01:30:19.600 --> 01:30:21.101
You have fun with Auntie?

1414
01:30:21.102 --> 01:30:22.686
Yeah. I had fun.

1415
01:30:22.687 --> 01:30:24.897
That's good. She's nice. huh?

1416
01:30:29.610 --> 01:30:30.736
Is that for me?

1417
01:30:32.697 --> 01:30:33.698
Thank you.

1418
01:30:39.620 --> 01:30:41.705
- Akiko?
- Hmm?

1419
01:30:41.706 --> 01:30:44.333
There's us. but who's this?

1420
01:30:45.084 --> 01:30:46.084
Is that Mom?

1421
01:30:47.170 --> 01:30:49.338
Uh-huh. Mom's right there.

1422
01:30:50.756 --> 01:30:51.757
Look at that.

1423
01:30:53.384 --> 01:30:54.719
You're so talented.

1424
01:30:58.890 --> 01:30:59.891
[Akiko sniffles]

1425
01:31:01.976 --> 01:31:02.976
[sniffles]

1426
01:31:04.020 --> 01:31:05.187
[solemn music playing]

1427
01:31:05.188 --> 01:31:07.356
What's wrong? Why are you sad?

1428
01:31:07.899 --> 01:31:09.233
[crying]

1429
01:31:12.653 --> 01:31:13.738
What is it?

1430
01:31:14.530 --> 01:31:15.531
Akiko.

1431
01:31:16.324 --> 01:31:18.367
It's okay. Hey.

1432
01:31:20.161 --> 01:31:21.161
It's okay.

1433
01:31:21.913 --> 01:31:23.039
Hey. I'm here.

1434
01:31:24.123 --> 01:31:25.583
I'll always be here for you.

1435
01:31:28.544 --> 01:31:30.087
[solemn music continues]

1436
01:32:07.959 --> 01:32:09.377
[solemn music continues]

1437
01:32:41.867 --> 01:32:43.286
Tachibana-san.

1438
01:32:45.121 --> 01:32:46.330
Is it ready?

1439
01:32:50.126 --> 01:32:51.168
Give me a minute.

1440
01:33:03.347 --> 01:33:04.974
There's the bomb you asked for.

1441
01:33:06.309 --> 01:33:08.602
Two machine guns. 140 kilos.

1442
01:33:08.603 --> 01:33:10.937
120 rounds. 80 kilos.

1443
01:33:10.938 --> 01:33:13.608
And we pulled out the main
fuel tank. dropping 400.

1444
01:33:14.233 --> 01:33:16.651
Instead. you've got a
number 25 bomb in the nose

1445
01:33:16.652 --> 01:33:18.738
and a number 50 in the fuselage.

1446
01:33:19.989 --> 01:33:23.075
Good. Now I have a chance to
finally make things right.

1447
01:33:24.744 --> 01:33:25.744
[rattling]

1448
01:33:26.912 --> 01:33:28.122
[rattling]

1449
01:33:32.543 --> 01:33:33.543
[chuckles softly]

1450
01:33:37.673 --> 01:33:38.841
The funny thing is...

1451
01:33:43.512 --> 01:33:45.890
I guess there's a part
of me that wants to live.

1452
01:33:46.932 --> 01:33:48.184
[chuckling]

1453
01:33:50.311 --> 01:33:52.605
No one on the Odo Island
crew wanted to die.

1454
01:33:54.065 --> 01:33:55.816
But <i>they</i> didn't get to go home.

1455
01:33:57.360 --> 01:33:58.610
None of them.

1456
01:33:58.611 --> 01:34:00.112
They didn't get the chance

1457
01:34:00.988 --> 01:34:02.865
because that
monster killed them.

1458
01:34:04.659 --> 01:34:06.327
I know what I have to do.

1459
01:34:29.308 --> 01:34:31.894
This was drawn by
a girl named Akiko.

1460
01:34:33.771 --> 01:34:35.815
I want there to be
a future for her.

1461
01:34:40.319 --> 01:34:41.946
Godzilla has to be stopped.

1462
01:34:42.446 --> 01:34:43.906
I'll do whatever it takes.

1463
01:34:44.949 --> 01:34:47.076
Well. then. I guess
you're finally ready.

1464
01:34:49.286 --> 01:34:50.329
Now... [sighs]

1465
01:34:51.664 --> 01:34:53.290
this is important. Listen up.

1466
01:34:53.874 --> 01:34:54.874
Down here.

1467
01:34:56.210 --> 01:34:58.087
This is the safety
for the bombs.

1468
01:34:58.879 --> 01:35:01.674
Pull it right before you
fly into its mouth. Got it?

1469
01:35:03.843 --> 01:35:04.844
One more thing.

1470
01:35:14.645 --> 01:35:16.272
Oh. Akiko?

1471
01:35:18.816 --> 01:35:21.193
Why are you out
here? Are you alone?

1472
01:35:22.486 --> 01:35:23.486
Look.

1473
01:35:30.619 --> 01:35:32.121
TO SUMIKO

1474
01:35:44.759 --> 01:35:49.221
LOOK AFTER AKIKO USE
THIS MONEY FOR HER

1475
01:35:56.687 --> 01:35:58.481
Is it from Daddy?

1476
01:35:59.899 --> 01:36:01.650
Huh? From Daddy?

1477
01:36:02.318 --> 01:36:03.318
Here.

1478
01:36:04.570 --> 01:36:06.946
It's all right. Don't
worry. sweetheart.

1479
01:36:06.947 --> 01:36:08.240
[water lapping gently]

1480
01:36:11.410 --> 01:36:14.163
[water plopping]

1481
01:36:14.872 --> 01:36:16.415
[beacon crackling]

1482
01:36:24.089 --> 01:36:26.966
Kuroshio 12 here. We see
floating deep-sea fish.

1483
01:36:26.967 --> 01:36:30.471
35.03 north. 139.41 east.

1484
01:36:41.190 --> 01:36:44.068
[Godzilla voice
recording playing]

1485
01:36:47.863 --> 01:36:49.113
[air-raid siren wailing]

1486
01:36:49.114 --> 01:36:52.200
[man 1 over speaker] <i>Godzilla
has been sighted in Sagami Bay.</i>

1487
01:36:52.201 --> 01:36:55.537
<i>The underwater decoy team
is deploying the audio lure</i>

1488
01:36:55.538 --> 01:36:57.748
<i>to bring it to the target area.</i>

1489
01:36:58.332 --> 01:37:01.000
<i>- All ships expedite schedules.</i>
- [man 2] Take only essentials!

1490
01:37:01.001 --> 01:37:03.378
[man 1] <i>Leave port as soon
as everyone is aboard.</i>

1491
01:37:03.379 --> 01:37:04.879
We'd better go.

1492
01:37:04.880 --> 01:37:06.215
[man 3] Move! Move! Move!

1493
01:37:06.799 --> 01:37:10.677
- Looks like Mizushima finally gave up.
- I feel bad. but it's for his own good.

1494
01:37:10.678 --> 01:37:13.555
To be honest. I didn't want
Shikishima flying either.

1495
01:37:13.556 --> 01:37:16.057
I'm worried he could do
something reckless today.

1496
01:37:16.058 --> 01:37:17.058
I don't want that.

1497
01:37:17.059 --> 01:37:19.812
He's got Akiko. He can't
just leave her alone.

1498
01:37:20.396 --> 01:37:21.938
[distant booming]

1499
01:37:21.939 --> 01:37:23.399
[fearful gasping]

1500
01:37:27.444 --> 01:37:28.445
[man 4 screams]

1501
01:37:30.364 --> 01:37:33.157
[man 1] <i>The underwater decoy
team has been destroyed!</i>

1502
01:37:33.158 --> 01:37:38.497
<i>Godzilla has entered Sagami Bay!
Wada Tsumi ships. leave port at once!</i>

1503
01:37:39.164 --> 01:37:40.164
Look.

1504
01:37:41.083 --> 01:37:42.084
There it is.

1505
01:37:42.585 --> 01:37:43.878
[Noda] It's already here.

1506
01:37:44.503 --> 01:37:46.422
[bombs exploding]

1507
01:37:55.431 --> 01:37:57.807
[man 1 on radio] <i>Godzilla's
through the final line of defense!</i>

1508
01:37:57.808 --> 01:37:59.101
<i>It's heading for shore!</i>

1509
01:38:00.227 --> 01:38:01.227
That's my signal.

1510
01:38:09.194 --> 01:38:11.113
[resolute music playing]

1511
01:38:25.002 --> 01:38:26.337
[resolute music continues]

1512
01:38:56.450 --> 01:38:58.619
Get out there and put
an end to this war.

1513
01:38:59.703 --> 01:39:00.704
Shikishima.

1514
01:39:01.288 --> 01:39:03.623
[man 1 over speaker]
<i>Everyone. leave port now!</i>

1515
01:39:03.624 --> 01:39:06.417
<i>Repeat. all Wada Tsumi
ships are to finish boarding</i>

1516
01:39:06.418 --> 01:39:08.379
<i>and leave port immediately!</i>

1517
01:39:09.254 --> 01:39:10.589
[waves crashing]

1518
01:39:14.051 --> 01:39:15.386
What now. Doc?

1519
01:39:16.136 --> 01:39:17.887
It's too late to do anything.

1520
01:39:17.888 --> 01:39:21.015
No. we just have to keep going.
The Sagami Trench is key.

1521
01:39:21.016 --> 01:39:23.559
There's nowhere else
suitable to execute our plan.

1522
01:39:23.560 --> 01:39:24.894
But we need to be there.

1523
01:39:24.895 --> 01:39:28.439
We have to rely on Shiki-san
to lure it out to us!

1524
01:39:28.440 --> 01:39:30.609
- Yes. sir!
- All right. let's go!

1525
01:39:31.318 --> 01:39:33.237
[resolute music continues]

1526
01:39:46.917 --> 01:39:48.877
Noda-san! Shikishima's calling!

1527
01:39:50.796 --> 01:39:53.047
Shikishima here. I've
taken off successfully.

1528
01:39:53.048 --> 01:39:55.508
I'll start to lure Godzilla
to the target area.

1529
01:39:55.509 --> 01:39:57.677
Good. We'll make sure
that we're ready for you.

1530
01:39:57.678 --> 01:40:01.889
- [Shikishima] <i>Get to the target quickly.</i>
- Shikishima! You better not try anything!

1531
01:40:01.890 --> 01:40:04.226
I won't let you abandon
Akiko. you got that?

1532
01:40:07.312 --> 01:40:09.023
Do you hear me. Shikishima?

1533
01:40:10.941 --> 01:40:13.193
Nothing. What is he thinking?

1534
01:40:13.902 --> 01:40:15.404
[resolute music continues]

1535
01:40:32.504 --> 01:40:35.382
One. two. One. two.

1536
01:40:36.133 --> 01:40:37.176
[man] Telegram!

1537
01:40:39.011 --> 01:40:40.011
Oh.

1538
01:40:46.727 --> 01:40:48.896
- Yes?
- [man] Mrs. Shikishima?

1539
01:40:51.523 --> 01:40:52.900
- A telegram for you.
- Oh.

1540
01:41:01.200 --> 01:41:02.743
[resolute music intensifies]

1541
01:41:07.206 --> 01:41:08.499
[footstep booming]

1542
01:41:11.376 --> 01:41:13.337
[terrified screaming]

1543
01:41:15.255 --> 01:41:16.464
[dog barking]

1544
01:41:16.465 --> 01:41:17.549
[dog yelping]

1545
01:41:24.807 --> 01:41:26.100
[determined sigh]

1546
01:41:31.063 --> 01:41:32.272
[Godzilla growls]

1547
01:41:37.111 --> 01:41:38.153
[Godzilla grunts]

1548
01:41:54.503 --> 01:41:55.503
[grunts]

1549
01:41:55.879 --> 01:41:58.006
[resolute music continues]

1550
01:42:16.775 --> 01:42:18.317
[Akitsu] Look at that.

1551
01:42:18.318 --> 01:42:20.195
Nice job. Shikishima.

1552
01:42:20.904 --> 01:42:24.365
It worked. And Godzilla doesn't
look too happy. does it?

1553
01:42:24.366 --> 01:42:25.450
Now's our chance.

1554
01:42:26.118 --> 01:42:27.369
It's up to us now.

1555
01:42:30.747 --> 01:42:32.331
All ships. prepare for battle!

1556
01:42:32.332 --> 01:42:34.932
- [man 1] You heard. battle positions!
- [man 2] Battle positions!

1557
01:42:37.212 --> 01:42:38.422
Freon cylinders ready!

1558
01:42:39.006 --> 01:42:41.549
46-centimeter shells ready!
Flotation switch ready!

1559
01:42:41.550 --> 01:42:43.176
Cables look good!

1560
01:42:43.177 --> 01:42:45.553
Circuits are a go. We
are ready when you are.

1561
01:42:45.554 --> 01:42:48.390
We're turning on the power!
Release the safety device!

1562
01:43:04.907 --> 01:43:07.075
That's right. I see you.

1563
01:43:09.077 --> 01:43:11.913
- All right. team one. Get out there.
- Team one. attack!

1564
01:43:11.914 --> 01:43:13.247
Team one. attack!

1565
01:43:13.248 --> 01:43:15.918
[siren wailing]

1566
01:43:20.589 --> 01:43:22.007
[siren continues wailing]

1567
01:43:34.853 --> 01:43:37.189
- [dorsal fins clunking]
- [radiation buzzing]

1568
01:43:44.321 --> 01:43:45.656
That's it.

1569
01:43:46.907 --> 01:43:48.659
[Godzilla snarling]

1570
01:43:54.748 --> 01:43:56.792
[steering wheel creaking]

1571
01:44:01.755 --> 01:44:02.755
[quiet rumbling]

1572
01:44:03.799 --> 01:44:04.799
[booming]

1573
01:44:04.800 --> 01:44:06.050
[gasping]

1574
01:44:06.051 --> 01:44:07.094
[men screaming]

1575
01:44:11.431 --> 01:44:13.183
[ominous music playing]

1576
01:44:18.647 --> 01:44:19.815
[grunting]

1577
01:44:22.651 --> 01:44:25.237
Holy hell. So
that's its heat ray.

1578
01:44:25.862 --> 01:44:27.947
- [growls softly]
- [flesh sizzling]

1579
01:44:27.948 --> 01:44:30.157
[man 1] The ships will
never survive this.

1580
01:44:30.158 --> 01:44:33.327
Listen. sir. We should evacuate
while there's still time.

1581
01:44:33.328 --> 01:44:36.289
No! At least not yet. We need
to start while we still can.

1582
01:44:36.290 --> 01:44:38.207
Doctor. it'll shoot
the heat ray again!

1583
01:44:38.208 --> 01:44:39.583
Not for a while.

1584
01:44:39.584 --> 01:44:42.379
Once Godzilla fires its heat
ray. it has to recharge.

1585
01:44:43.005 --> 01:44:44.214
We have to go!

1586
01:44:45.340 --> 01:44:46.674
Start the operation. now!

1587
01:44:46.675 --> 01:44:48.593
[resolute music playing]

1588
01:44:49.928 --> 01:44:51.096
[Hotta inhales deeply]

1589
01:44:52.097 --> 01:44:54.266
Wada Tsumi is a go!
That's an order!

1590
01:44:54.975 --> 01:44:56.393
[resolute music continues]

1591
01:44:59.021 --> 01:45:00.647
[ship horn sounds]

1592
01:45:12.701 --> 01:45:16.872
Freon and flotation units. stand
by. On my order. begin launch!

1593
01:45:19.958 --> 01:45:21.376
[metal creaking]

1594
01:45:24.379 --> 01:45:25.797
[resolute music continues]

1595
01:45:42.272 --> 01:45:43.273
Shiki-san!

1596
01:45:47.444 --> 01:45:49.363
[breathing shakily]

1597
01:45:57.954 --> 01:46:00.123
[Godzilla snarling]

1598
01:46:09.716 --> 01:46:11.968
- [man 1] Crane fully deployed!
- [Hotta] Roger!

1599
01:46:12.594 --> 01:46:15.262
We need to maintain our
course. Call the Hibiki!

1600
01:46:15.263 --> 01:46:17.140
[man 1] Hibiki. maintain course!

1601
01:46:17.724 --> 01:46:20.894
We're going to take a little
damage. Stay at our current speed!

1602
01:46:22.479 --> 01:46:24.564
[tense music playing]

1603
01:46:25.399 --> 01:46:27.692
[man 1] Hibiki closing
in! Four meters!

1604
01:46:28.944 --> 01:46:29.945
Two meters!

1605
01:46:30.612 --> 01:46:33.740
- Brace for impact! Hold on!
- [man 1] Brace for impact!

1606
01:46:36.868 --> 01:46:39.162
[metal crunching]

1607
01:46:48.380 --> 01:46:50.756
Crossing successful!
Full speed ahead!

1608
01:46:50.757 --> 01:46:53.175
[man 1] Full speed! Full speed!

1609
01:46:53.176 --> 01:46:54.886
[dramatic music playing]

1610
01:47:01.518 --> 01:47:03.562
[Godzilla snarling]

1611
01:47:07.941 --> 01:47:10.152
Good. Good!

1612
01:47:11.194 --> 01:47:13.155
- Go get the switch ready!
- On it!

1613
01:47:17.868 --> 01:47:20.245
[Godzilla growling]

1614
01:47:21.621 --> 01:47:23.539
What's it doing? We ready?

1615
01:47:23.540 --> 01:47:25.124
[Godzilla's heat ray charging]

1616
01:47:25.125 --> 01:47:26.334
We're close.

1617
01:47:34.634 --> 01:47:36.344
[Noda breathing heavily]

1618
01:47:37.554 --> 01:47:38.847
Oy...

1619
01:47:48.440 --> 01:47:50.442
- Hit it. Captain!
- Roger that!

1620
01:47:52.652 --> 01:47:54.279
- The Freon!
- Got it!

1621
01:48:10.921 --> 01:48:13.298
[man 1] Depth. 1.200 meters!

1622
01:48:14.341 --> 01:48:15.509
1.300!

1623
01:48:16.134 --> 01:48:17.719
- 1.400!
- That's it!

1624
01:48:18.261 --> 01:48:19.930
- [man 1] 1.450 meters!
- That's it!

1625
01:48:21.139 --> 01:48:22.640
[man 1] 1.500!

1626
01:48:22.641 --> 01:48:25.100
That's our target
depth! We've reached it.

1627
01:48:25.101 --> 01:48:27.103
[determined breathing]

1628
01:48:30.398 --> 01:48:31.482
[music stops]

1629
01:48:31.483 --> 01:48:32.943
[anticipatory silence]

1630
01:48:37.197 --> 01:48:40.032
We did it! We sunk Godzilla!

1631
01:48:40.033 --> 01:48:41.493
Was that it?

1632
01:48:43.578 --> 01:48:44.912
[cable straining]

1633
01:48:44.913 --> 01:48:46.164
[shocked gasping]

1634
01:48:48.750 --> 01:48:50.627
Guess the big guy won't quit.

1635
01:48:51.169 --> 01:48:53.629
- We... we need to go to plan B.
- Yes. hurry.

1636
01:48:53.630 --> 01:48:54.923
[Noda grunts softly]

1637
01:48:56.716 --> 01:48:58.969
[grunting. strained groaning]

1638
01:49:09.896 --> 01:49:11.898
[tense music playing]

1639
01:49:12.524 --> 01:49:14.275
That's it. now rise!

1640
01:49:14.276 --> 01:49:16.444
[man 2] Depth. 1.200 meters!

1641
01:49:17.028 --> 01:49:19.322
1.100! 1.000!

1642
01:49:25.912 --> 01:49:27.080
[cable pings]

1643
01:49:27.956 --> 01:49:31.960
The cables have stopped! The
current depth is 803 meters!

1644
01:49:33.503 --> 01:49:35.338
What's wrong? Why's it stopping?

1645
01:49:38.049 --> 01:49:39.342
[ominous music playing]

1646
01:49:40.051 --> 01:49:41.469
It bit through it.

1647
01:49:44.639 --> 01:49:47.016
Hibiki. we're going to
have to pull Godzilla up!

1648
01:49:47.017 --> 01:49:48.767
Maximum speed. 90 degrees!

1649
01:49:48.768 --> 01:49:51.437
But. sir. even with both ships.
we don't have enough power.

1650
01:49:51.438 --> 01:49:55.024
I don't give a damn! Give
it all you can. gentlemen.

1651
01:49:55.025 --> 01:49:56.318
[all] Yes. sir!

1652
01:49:58.486 --> 01:50:00.488
[tense music continues]

1653
01:50:13.168 --> 01:50:14.502
We can't keep going!

1654
01:50:15.003 --> 01:50:16.754
The cranes won't
hold much longer!

1655
01:50:16.755 --> 01:50:18.255
[scared yelling]

1656
01:50:18.256 --> 01:50:19.549
[screaming]

1657
01:50:20.383 --> 01:50:21.551
[panicked screaming]

1658
01:50:22.594 --> 01:50:23.970
[disquieting music playing]

1659
01:50:29.434 --> 01:50:31.019
[music intensifies]

1660
01:50:34.022 --> 01:50:35.231
[man 3 gasps]

1661
01:50:38.193 --> 01:50:40.444
[ship horn blares]

1662
01:50:40.445 --> 01:50:44.366
<i>Greetings! This is the
Fujimaru from Yokohama Eisen.</i>

1663
01:50:45.075 --> 01:50:47.701
<i>You boys look like you
could use some help!</i>

1664
01:50:47.702 --> 01:50:48.912
I know that voice.

1665
01:50:49.746 --> 01:50:52.540
Mizushima here.
Captain. are you there?

1666
01:50:53.917 --> 01:50:55.835
Kid. is that you?

1667
01:50:56.586 --> 01:50:57.628
[chuckling] Yeah!

1668
01:50:57.629 --> 01:51:00.547
<i>This is the Koeimaru
from Toyo Balloon.</i>

1669
01:51:00.548 --> 01:51:01.466
<i>Need a hand?</i>

1670
01:51:01.467 --> 01:51:05.094
<i>And the Nikkomaru from Yokohama
Eisen! At your service!</i>

1671
01:51:05.095 --> 01:51:08.138
<i>- The Daisan Shiokazemaru. Here to help.
- The Tetsuyumaru here.</i>

1672
01:51:08.139 --> 01:51:10.099
<i>- And the Nanamimaru.
- Minamimaru here.</i>

1673
01:51:10.100 --> 01:51:11.600
<i>- Kisshomaru.
- Junseimaru.</i>

1674
01:51:11.601 --> 01:51:13.060
<i>- Wakamaru.
- Heimitsumaru.</i>

1675
01:51:13.061 --> 01:51:14.395
<i>Tenyumaru.</i>

1676
01:51:14.396 --> 01:51:16.021
<i>- Kaiomaru.
- Hyuga.</i>

1677
01:51:16.022 --> 01:51:17.356
<i>- Choukamaru.
- Shoseimaru.</i>

1678
01:51:17.357 --> 01:51:18.774
<i>- Taramaru.
- Yasakamaru.</i>

1679
01:51:18.775 --> 01:51:21.861
How's this for useless? We're
here to save your asses.

1680
01:51:22.821 --> 01:51:25.030
Ah. Let's do this!

1681
01:51:25.031 --> 01:51:26.408
Look at that!

1682
01:51:27.075 --> 01:51:29.494
I guess he decided not
to listen to us. huh?

1683
01:51:29.994 --> 01:51:33.331
All right. tugboats. Ready?
We've got to pull up Godzilla!

1684
01:51:33.873 --> 01:51:35.541
[man 4] All ships. pull!

1685
01:51:35.542 --> 01:51:37.293
[man 5] All ships. pull!

1686
01:51:38.753 --> 01:51:40.046
[creaking]

1687
01:51:44.759 --> 01:51:46.761
[tenacious music playing]

1688
01:51:58.314 --> 01:51:59.941
[metal creaking]

1689
01:52:02.277 --> 01:52:05.238
It's working! Godzilla
is climbing again!

1690
01:52:07.198 --> 01:52:10.075
All right. there it
is. Ya like that? Huh?

1691
01:52:10.076 --> 01:52:12.537
[man 1] Current
depth. 700 meters!

1692
01:52:13.413 --> 01:52:15.123
Go on. That's it. that's it.

1693
01:52:16.040 --> 01:52:17.625
[tenacious music continues]

1694
01:52:29.512 --> 01:52:31.598
[Godzilla snarling]

1695
01:52:33.016 --> 01:52:35.059
[Godzilla roaring]

1696
01:52:38.271 --> 01:52:39.314
[screaming]

1697
01:52:40.648 --> 01:52:41.691
[strained grunting]

1698
01:52:43.026 --> 01:52:46.321
[roaring]

1699
01:52:46.821 --> 01:52:47.947
He's still standing!

1700
01:52:48.782 --> 01:52:51.074
Evasive actions! We need to go!

1701
01:52:51.075 --> 01:52:52.494
[dramatic music playing]

1702
01:53:09.803 --> 01:53:11.804
[music fades]

1703
01:53:11.805 --> 01:53:13.139
[inaudible]

1704
01:53:15.558 --> 01:53:18.520
[inaudible]

1705
01:53:35.578 --> 01:53:36.955
[resolute music playing]

1706
01:53:41.918 --> 01:53:44.712
- Hey. What's he doing?
- Wait. Is he... is...

1707
01:53:48.550 --> 01:53:50.260
- Don't do it!
- Stop. kid!

1708
01:53:50.844 --> 01:53:52.344
[yelling] Shikishima!

1709
01:53:52.345 --> 01:53:54.430
[determined breathing]

1710
01:54:08.152 --> 01:54:09.988
[music stops]

1711
01:54:19.581 --> 01:54:20.582
Shikishima...

1712
01:54:22.750 --> 01:54:24.127
[disbelieving muttering]

1713
01:54:35.930 --> 01:54:37.473
Look! Right there!

1714
01:54:39.350 --> 01:54:40.810
[ethereal music playing]

1715
01:54:42.145 --> 01:54:43.271
There he is.

1716
01:54:43.897 --> 01:54:45.105
[relieved chuckling]

1717
01:54:45.106 --> 01:54:46.316
There he is!

1718
01:54:49.110 --> 01:54:52.238
[man on radio] <i>Pilot...
ejected! He's alive!</i>

1719
01:54:53.990 --> 01:54:55.116
[relieved sigh]

1720
01:54:55.825 --> 01:54:57.201
[breathing shakily]

1721
01:55:00.997 --> 01:55:03.541
I added this too.
It's an ejection seat.

1722
01:55:05.001 --> 01:55:06.753
You pull that lever
to activate it.

1723
01:55:09.339 --> 01:55:10.339
[Shikishima gasps]

1724
01:55:10.340 --> 01:55:11.424
Live.

1725
01:55:14.135 --> 01:55:15.302
Tachibana-san.

1726
01:55:15.303 --> 01:55:16.804
[ethereal music building]

1727
01:55:18.890 --> 01:55:20.266
[relieved sobbing]

1728
01:55:23.978 --> 01:55:24.978
[coughs softly]

1729
01:55:27.649 --> 01:55:29.317
[guttural growling]

1730
01:55:47.126 --> 01:55:49.128
[ethereal music continues]

1731
01:56:28.001 --> 01:56:29.585
[excited chattering]

1732
01:56:45.935 --> 01:56:47.145
[Mizushima] Shikishima!

1733
01:56:52.233 --> 01:56:53.568
[sobbing] You did it!

1734
01:56:54.944 --> 01:56:55.944
You did it!

1735
01:56:57.947 --> 01:56:59.156
[Akitsu] Nice work. Kid.

1736
01:56:59.157 --> 01:57:00.867
[Mizushima and Akitsu laughing]

1737
01:57:03.202 --> 01:57:04.120
Sumiko.

1738
01:57:04.121 --> 01:57:05.204
